{"title_page": "MediaMarkt", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Media market}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name=Media-Saturn Holding GmbH\n| logo             = Media Markt logo.svg\n| logo_caption     = Media Markt Logo\n| logo_size        = 260px\n| type             = Subsidiary\n| industry         = [[Retail]]\n| foundation       = 1979\n| founder          = {{unbulleted list|Leopold Stiefel|Walter Gunz|[[Erich Kellerhals]]|Helga Kellerhals}}\n| location_city    = [[Ingolstadt]]\n| location_country = [[Germany]]\n| products         = [[Consumer electronics]]\n| locations        = 1042 in 14 European countries\n| parent           = [[Ceconomy]]\n| revenue          = \u20ac21,5 billion (2018/19)<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ceconomy.de/media/ceconomy_geschaeftsbericht_2018_19.pdf |title=Ceconomy}}</ref>\n| homepage         = {{URL|www.mediamarkt.com}}\n}}\n[[File:20131001 herstal05.JPG|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Herstal, Belgium]]\n'''Media Markt''' is a [[Germany|German]] multinational chain of stores selling [[consumer electronics]] with over 1000 stores in [[Europe]]. With chain of stores Saturn it constitutes Media-Saturn Holding, owned by the retail trade company Ceconomy, which was demerged from [[Metro AG|Metro Group]] in 2017.\n\n==History==\n\nMedia Markt was founded by entrepreneurs Leopold Stiefel, Walter Gunz, Erich Kellerhals, and Helga Kellerhals. The first store opened on 24 November 1979 in [[Munich]]. By 1985, nine other stores had opened near Munich. \n\nIn 1988 Kaufhof Warenhaus AG acquired a 54 percent majority in the holding company of the media stores founded in 1979. In 1989 expansion began in neighboring countries. Media Markt took over the competing retail chain Saturn in 1990, in which [[Kaufhof]] was already involved. In 1996 Kaufhof Holding, [[Metro Cash & Carry]], Deutsche SB-Kauf AG and the German department store Asko AG (where a Metro holding company had previously each held shares) merged and formed Metro AG. Since the merger into the MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group, Media Markt and Saturn have been managed as independent brands in a centrally controlled group.\n\nIn January 2013, Metro had around 78% of the shares. The Kellerhals family owned 21.67% through their indirectly held holding company Convergenta Invest.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/handel/a-879986.html |title=Media-Saturn-Mitgr\u00fcnder verkauft an Metro |publisher=manager-magazin.de |date=28 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nSince 2017 Media-Saturn Holding which consisting of Media Markt and [[Saturn (store)|Saturn]] chains is owned by [[Ceconomy]], an company formed through a demerger from [[Metro AG|Metro Group]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://archiv.metrogroup.de/en/press-releases/2017/07/12/demerger-of-metro-group-completed|title=Demerger of METRO Group completed - New METRO and CECONOMY commence trading at the stock exchange tomorrow|publisher=METRO AG|date=2017-07-12|access-date=2017-11-13|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Operations ==\n[[File:Media_Markt_Weiterstadt.JPG|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Weiterstadt, Germany]]\n\nIn 2012, the company launched its online shop, starting with Germany in January.\n\nIn Italy is used Media World brand instead of Media Markt.\n\n=== Franchise model ===\nEvery store is 10% owned by the store manager. Store manag\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\ners have discretion as to which products to stock, range, pricing, personnel and material costs. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Country !! Stores\n|-\n| Germany || 274\n|-\n| Italy || 110\n|-\n| Poland || 90\n|-\n| Spain ||\n87<ref>http://specials.mediamarkt.es/tiendas</ref>\n|-\n| Turkey || 72<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediamarkt.com.tr/|title=MediaMarkt - Avrupa'n\u0131n 1 Numaral\u0131 Elektronik Perakendecisi|website=www.mediamarkt.com.tr}}</ref>\n|-\n| Netherlands || 50\n|-\n| Austria || 47\n|-\n| Hungary || 32\n|-\n| Sweden || 27\n|-\n| Switzerland || 26\n|-\n| Belgium || 24\n|-\n| Greece || 12<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediamarkt.gr/|title=Media Markt eShop|website=www.mediamarkt.gr}}</ref>\n|-\n| Portugal || 9\n|}\n\nIn july 2007 Ceconomy bought 24% stake in French multinational [[Fnac Darty]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spglobal.com/marketintelligence/en/news-insights/trending/j6ovkjsj34yem-fijxupmg2 |title=CECONOMY buys 24% Fnac Darty stake for \u20ac452 million |publisher=spglobal.com |date=26 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nCeconomy sold the 46 stores in [[Russia]] to [[M.video]] in exchange of 15% in the Russian retailer. <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ceconomy-m-video/germanys-ceconomy-to-swap-russian-business-for-m-video-stake-idUSKBN1JG12C |title=Germany's Ceconomy to swap Russian business for M.video stake |publisher=Reuters.com |date=20 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn November 17th, 2010 the first Media Markt was opened in Huai Hai Road, [[Shanghai]], [[China]]. Six more stores followed, which were realized together with [[Foxconn]] through a joint venture. In January 2013, it became known that Media Markt would withdraw from China because the Metro Group would not be able to raise the capital necessary for its further expansion.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/handel/a-877788.html |title=Media Markt scheitert in China |publisher=manager-magazin.de |date=26 July 2017</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-03/13/content_16305383.htm|title=Media Markt closes all Chinese stores - Business - Chinadaily.com.cn|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref>\n\n==Advertising==\n[[File:Media Markt Oldenburg (2018) 07.jpg|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Oldenburg, Germany]]\n[[File:Media-markt-automat.jpg|thumb|350px|Media Markt vending machine at Hamburg Airport, Germany]] \nMedia Markt had an aggressive advertising similar to American companies and also a few controversial commercials in 2000's. It is known in [[Germany]] for its humorous, but sometimes crude, [[advertising]] campaigns; for example, the slogan \"''Lasst euch nicht verarschen''\" meaning \"Don't let yourself be conned\", literally verbal prefix ''for-'' (ver-) + ass (Arsch) + infinitive suffix ''-en'' (-en).\n\nThe well-known advertising campaigns of the brands Media Markt and Saturn are designed by the internal marketing organization redblue Marketing GmbH in Munich .\n\n===Slogan===\n\nMedia Markt's main slogan \"''Ich bin doch nicht bl\u00f6d''\" (Hey, I'm not stupid) has been translated into the languages of the other countries where the company operates, except Italy and Poland:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Language || Slogan\n|-\n| [[German language|German]] || Ich bin doch nicht bl\u00f6d. (''I'm not stupid.'')\n|-\n| [[Spanish language|Spanish]] || \u00a1Yo no soy tonto! (''I am not a fool!'')\n|-\n| [[Dutch language|Dutch]] || Ik ben toch niet gek (''I'm not crazy'')\n|-\n| [[French language|French]] || Je ne suis pas fou. (''I'm not crazy'')\n|-\n| [[Galician language|Galician]] || Eu non son parvo! (''I am not a fool!'')\n|-\n| [[Greek language|Greek]] || \u0394\u03b5\u03bd \u03b5\u03af\u03bc\u03b1\u03b9 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c7\u03c4\u03b5\u03c3\u03b9\u03bd\u03cc\u03c2! (''I was not born yesterday'')\n|-\n| [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] || Mert h\u00fclye az\u00e9rt nem vagyok! (''Because I'm not stupid'')\n|-\n| [[Italian language|Italian]] || Non sono mica scemo! (''I am not stupid!''){{efn|This slogan is used in the Italophone Switzerland}}, Voglio il mondo (''I want the world'')\n|-\n| [[Polish language|Polish]] || Nieludzko niskie ceny. (''Inhumanly low prices.'')\n|-\n| [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] || Eu \u00e9 que n\u00e3o sou parvo! (''It's not me who's a fool!'')\n|-\n| [[Swedish language|Swedish]] || Allt annat k\u00e4nns puckat! (''Everything else seems stupid!'')\n|-\n| [[Catalan language|Catalan]] || Jo no s\u00f3c tonto! (''I am not stupid'')\n|-\n| [[Basque language|Basque]] || Ni ez naiz inozoa! (''I am not stupid'')\n|-\n| [[Turkish language|Turkish]] || Bakmadan Almam. (''I don't buy without looking.'')\n|-\n| [[Russian language|Russian]] || \u0414\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0439, \u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0439 - \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0435\u043c \u0432\u044b\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0439! (''Go on, choose with your heart'')\n|}\n\n===2006 World Cup advertising campaign===\n\nPrior to the [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006 World Cup]], Media Markt launched a campaign, claiming to be the \"best fan supplier\" (\"''Bester Fanausr\u00fcster''\"), with commercials showing international football fans shopping at Media Markt, showing exaggerated stereotypes of the participating countries, and making fun of the [[Austria national football team|Austria]] team, which did  not qualify. This included a French seductress, Dutch fans smoking [[marijuana]] in caravans, or a Saudi haggling - to pay more. German fans were portrayed with big bellies, asking for refrigerators to keep their beer cool, rather than looking for a new TV set.\n\nAn additional series of ads, promoting a rebate of \u20ac10 for each goal Germany scores (except [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-outs]]), showed international soccer fans begging the Germans to score as many goals as possible - against their own team.\n\nWhen the Netherlands lost to Portugal, Media Markt used a quote from a 1980s show featuring [[Rudi Carrell]], a Dutchman who was a long-time TV celebrity in Germany, to express ''[[Schadenfreude]]''. A [[FIFA World Cup Trophy|World Cup trophy]] is shown to grieving Dutch fans in their caravan with the comment \"This would have been your prize!\".\n\n===Polish advertising===\n[[File:Bydgoszcz Media Markt ulica Jagiello\u0144ska.jpg|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Bydgoszcz, Poland]]\nIn March 2006, the \"Poland version\" showed moustache-wearing Polish customers praising the shop for \"prices deep like Polish soul\" before hugging the German sales managers, who looked quite uncomfortable in the bear hugs. Afterwards, one of the Germans pointed out that his watch was still there, and that \"The Pole is an honest person, after all\". Then, the three men are shown to be missing their trousers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEjOWqXAI7Y |title=Media Markt nie dla Polak\u00f3w |publisher=Youtube.com |date=31 March 2011}}</ref>\n\nThis commercial caused a scandal in Poland, for the widely known German stereotype of Poles being thieves. Media Markt argued that the advertisements also made fun of other national clich\u00e9s, including Germans, and none of the other clich\u00e9s were perceived as negative towards the people they presented. Its aim was to exaggerate the clich\u00e9 of the Polish thief to dismiss it as unjustified prejudice, Media Markt claimed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.focus.msn.de/finanzen/news/proteste-aus-polen_nid_26829.html |title=Proteste aus Polen - Media Markt zieht Fernseh-Werbung zur\u00fcck |publisher=Focus.msn.de |date=28 March 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060516121929/focus.msn.de/finanzen/news/proteste-aus-polen_nid_26829.html |archive-date=16 May 2006}}</ref>\n\nThe store apologised and withdrew the advert after their Polish branch asked to do so, following protests in Poland, a call from the Polish embassy in Berlin and protests from German [[Polish diaspora|Polonia]].\n\n===Portuguese advertising===\n\nIn January 2008 Media Markt launched a campaign presenting a fictitious country called \"Dumb Land\", where several characters with [[Eastern Europe]]an accents were presented as being from this country, which even has an anthem. A central theme of this campaign presented a [[Boy Scout]] as an idiot. This really upset people as many consider Scouts to be responsible and valued members of society. An online petition was created to persuade Media Markt to withdraw the campaign and to offer a public apology. Due to this petition and a lot of pressure from the Scouting movement, Media Markt had to remove the Boy Scout from their campaign, including TV and radio ads.\n\n===Turkish advertising===\n\nTurkish Union Association in [[Eski\u015fehir]], [[Turkey]] motivated suspension of an advertisement campaign by the group on grounds that Media Markt \"[[Article 301 (Turkish Penal Code)|insulted Turkishness]]\" by depicting consumers that purchased overpriced merchandise with animal heads. A ban of the advertisements lasted for 3 months in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100825185814/http://www.hurriyetdailynew.com/n.php?n=did-animals-really-insult-turkishness-2009-10-22 |title=Ads criticized for insulting Turkishness with animal heads on humans |publisher=Hurriyetdailynews.com |date=22 October 2009 |accessdate=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100825185814/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/n.php?n=did-animals-really-insult-turkishness-2009-10-22 |archive-date=25 August 2010}}</ref> There have been many accusations on their official Facebook fan page about their false product advertisements in Turkey.\n\n=== Saubillig ===\n\nA former German campaign played on the German expression \"saubillig\" which means extremely cheap, but literally \"sow (female pig) cheap\". ''Sau-'' is a common emphasising prefix in colloquial German. Inside the stores the entrances were signposted as \"Schweingang\" = wordplay on the word Eingang (Entrance) and Schwein (pig), and the exit as \"Sausgang\" = wordplay on the word Ausgang (Exit) and the German word for sow (Sau) - the female pig.\n\n== Controversies ==\n=== Misleading advertising methods ===\n==== Article without VAT ====\nMedia Markt promised in 2005 a promotion to sell items \"without [[VAT]]\" (with a discount equal to VAT). In fact, the prices for these items had previously been increased in order to actually achieve the normal price. A competitor sued a branch in Mannheim.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ftd.de/unternehmen/handel_dienstleister/129743.html |title=Media-Markt mogelte bei Mehrwertsteuer |publisher=ftd.de |date=8 November 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224021702/http://www.ftd.de/unternehmen/handel_dienstleister/129743.html |archive-date=24 February 2007}}</ref>\n\n==== Decoy offers ====\nThe MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group has made [[bait-and-switch]] in the past : articles were advertised extensively at extremely low prices, but were sold out within a very short time. According to case law on the law against unfair competition(UWG) advertised special offers must be available for at least two days. Consumer advocates criticized that this was often not guaranteed at Media Markt and Saturn. The group denied that; there were only a few exceptions despite large stocks. It is generally difficult to provide concrete evidence of such cases, since consumer protection groups do not have access to the delivery dates of the companies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/lockvogel-angebote-gericht-knoepft-sich-media-markt-werbung-vor-a-481788.html |title=Gericht kn\u00f6pft sich Media-Markt-Werbung vor |publisher=spiegel.de |date=9 May 2007}}</ref>\n\n==== Price Guarantee  ====\nIn 2005, samples from the [[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]] in the Munich area showed that Media Markt or Saturn stores were more expensive in 15 out of 21 cases than local competitors. In Berlin they were 11 out of 21 cases. The MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group countered the allegations with a \"price guarantee\" that promised buyers a refund of the price difference if they found the product at a cheaper price in another shop.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.faz.net/aktuell/wirtschaft/unternehmen/einzelhandel-die-trickser-vom-media-markt-1303977.html |title=Die Trickser vom Media-Markt |publisher=faz.net |date=9 January 2006}}</ref>\n\n==== 0 -% - financing ====\nIn 2013, 0% financing from the Spanish bank [[Banco Santander]] was criticized. A credit loss insurance that costs 10% is taken out only on a note in the small print.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://helpv2.orf.at/stories/1714801/index.html |title=Kreditversicherung wider Willen |publisher=orf.at |date=23 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n=== The exclusive sale of Intel PCs ===\nAccording to research published by the [[Financial Times]] Germany in 2008, the MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group committed to [[Intel]] in 1999 to only sell PCs with Intel processors. The holding company received 85 million euros in purchase discounts and advertising grants from Intel in 2007 alone. The European antitrust authorities investigated the distortion of competition. Intel was fined 1.06 billion euros in May 2009 by the European Competition Commission for these and other antitrust violations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/wettbewerbsverstoesse-intels-praktiken-schockieren-kartellrechtler-a-624575.html |title=Intels Praktiken schockieren Kartellrechtler |publisher=spiegel.de |date=13 May 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe retail chain was moved by Intel's discount system to have only insignificant or no computers with [[AMD]] processors in the range. According to the [[European Commission]], Intel has made direct and indirect payments to MSH since 1997. The payments were subject to the condition that, if possible, only offer Intel systems.\n\n=== Body searches ===\n\nIn 2014, in [[Krems an der Donau]] in [[Lower Austria]], theft of the Media Markt, which is said to have been committed by employees, not only carried out bag checks, as is common in many companies, but also body searches on all employees. The unions see this as a violation of [[human dignity]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noe.orf.at/v2/news/stories/2624102/ |title=Leibesvisitation bei Mitarbeitern |publisher=orf.at |date=7 January 2014}}</ref> As a consequence, employees of other branches in Austria reported this procedure. This approach was blamed on the security service providers by the company.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noe.orf.at/v2/news/stories/2624466/ |title=Media Markt: Weitere Leibesvisitationen\n|publisher=orf.at |date=9 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Antitrust proceedings ===\n\nOn June 13, 2014, the Austrian Federal Competition Authority (BWB) announced a decision by the cartel court on April 23, 2014 against Media-Saturn BeteiligungsgmbH. A fine of EUR 1,230,000 was imposed for vertical price matching of [[retail price]]s with the electronics industry between October 2009 and early 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bwb.gv.at/KartelleUndMarkmachtmissbrauch/Entscheidungen/Seiten/Media-Saturn.aspx |title=BWB/K-302 Geldbu\u00dfenentscheidung gegen Media-Saturn BeteiligungsgmbH\n|publisher=bwb.gv.at |date=13 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928050906/http://www.bwb.gv.at/KartelleUndMarkmachtmissbrauch/Entscheidungen/Seiten/Media-Saturn.aspx |archive-date=28 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Media Markt}}\n* {{official|http://www.mediamarkt.com/ }}\n\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1979]]\n[[Category:Consumer electronics retailers of Germany]]\n[[Category:Retail companies of Germany]]\n[[Category:Metro Group]]\n[[Category:Scandals in Poland]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Media market}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name=Media-Saturn Holding GmbH\n| logo             = Media Markt logo.svg\n| logo_caption     = Media Markt Logo\n| logo_size        = 260px\n| type             = Subsidiary\n| industry         = [[Retail]]\n| foundation       = 1979\n| founder          = {{unbulleted list|Leopold Stiefel|Walter Gunz|[[Erich Kellerhals]]|Helga Kellerhals}}\n| location_city    = [[Ingolstadt]]\n| location_country = [[Germany]]\n| products         = [[Consumer electronics]]\n| locations        = 1042 in 14 European countries\n| parent           = [[Ceconomy]]\n| homepage         = {{URL|www.mediamarkt.com}}\n}}\n[[File:20131001 herstal05.JPG|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Herstal, Belgium]]\n'''Media Markt''' is a [[Germany|German]] multinational chain of stores selling [[consumer electronics]] with over 1000 stores in [[Europe]]. With chain of stores Saturn it constitutes Media-Saturn Holding, owned by the retail trade company Ceconomy, which was demerged from [[Metro AG|Metro Group]] in 2017.\n\n==History==\n\nMedia Markt was founded by entrepreneurs Leopold Stiefel, Walter Gunz, Erich Kellerhals, and Helga Kellerhals. The first store opened on 24 November 1979 in [[Munich]]. By 1985, nine other stores had opened near Munich. \n\nIn 1988 Kaufhof Warenhaus AG acquired a 54 percent majority in the holding company of the media stores founded in 1979. In 1989 expansion began in neighboring countries. Media Markt took over the competing retail chain Saturn in 1990, in which [[Kaufhof]] was already involved. In 1996 Kaufhof Holding, [[Metro Cash & Carry]], Deutsche SB-Kauf AG and the German department store Asko AG (where a Metro holding company had previously each held shares) merged and formed Metro AG. Since the merger into the MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group, Media Markt and Saturn have been managed as independent brands in a centrally controlled group.\n\nIn January 2013, Metro had around 78% of the shares. The Kellerhals family owned 21.67% through their indirectly held holding company Convergenta Invest.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/handel/a-879986.html |title=Media-Saturn-Mitgr\u00fcnder verkauft an Metro |publisher=manager-magazin.de |date=28 January 2013}}</ref>\n\nSince 2017 Media-Saturn Holding which consisting of Media Markt and [[Saturn (store)|Saturn]] chains is owned by [[Ceconomy]], an company formed through a demerger from [[Metro AG|Metro Group]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://archiv.metrogroup.de/en/press-releases/2017/07/12/demerger-of-metro-group-completed|title=Demerger of METRO Group completed - New METRO and CECONOMY commence trading at the stock exchange tomorrow|publisher=METRO AG|date=2017-07-12|access-date=2017-11-13|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n== Operations ==\n[[File:Media_Markt_Weiterstadt.JPG|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Weiterstadt, Germany]]\n\nIn 2012, the company launched its online shop, starting with Germany in January.\n\nIn Italy is used Media World brand instead of Media Markt.\n\n=== Franchise model ===\nEvery store is 10% owned by the store manager. Store manag\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\ners have discretion as to which products to stock, range, pricing, personnel and material costs. \n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Country !! Stores\n|-\n| Germany || 274\n|-\n| Italy || 110\n|-\n| Poland || 90\n|-\n| Spain ||\n87<ref>http://specials.mediamarkt.es/tiendas</ref>\n|-\n| Turkey || 72<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediamarkt.com.tr/|title=MediaMarkt - Avrupa'n\u0131n 1 Numaral\u0131 Elektronik Perakendecisi|website=www.mediamarkt.com.tr}}</ref>\n|-\n| Netherlands || 50\n|-\n| Austria || 47\n|-\n| Hungary || 32\n|-\n| Sweden || 27\n|-\n| Switzerland || 26\n|-\n| Belgium || 24\n|-\n| Greece || 12<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mediamarkt.gr/|title=Media Markt eShop|website=www.mediamarkt.gr}}</ref>\n|-\n| Portugal || 9\n|}\n\nIn july 2007 Ceconomy bought 24% stake in French multinational [[Fnac Darty]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spglobal.com/marketintelligence/en/news-insights/trending/j6ovkjsj34yem-fijxupmg2 |title=CECONOMY buys 24% Fnac Darty stake for \u20ac452 million |publisher=spglobal.com |date=26 July 2017}}</ref>\n\nCeconomy sold the 46 stores in [[Russia]] to [[M.video]] in exchange of 15% in the Russian retailer. <ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-ceconomy-m-video/germanys-ceconomy-to-swap-russian-business-for-m-video-stake-idUSKBN1JG12C |title=Germany's Ceconomy to swap Russian business for M.video stake |publisher=Reuters.com |date=20 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn November 17th, 2010 the first Media Markt was opened in Huai Hai Road, [[Shanghai]], [[China]]. Six more stores followed, which were realized together with [[Foxconn]] through a joint venture. In January 2013, it became known that Media Markt would withdraw from China because the Metro Group would not be able to raise the capital necessary for its further expansion.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.manager-magazin.de/unternehmen/handel/a-877788.html |title=Media Markt scheitert in China |publisher=manager-magazin.de |date=26 July 2017</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/2013-03/13/content_16305383.htm|title=Media Markt closes all Chinese stores - Business - Chinadaily.com.cn|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2020-01-18}}</ref>\n\n==Advertising==\n[[File:Media Markt Oldenburg (2018) 07.jpg|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Oldenburg, Germany]]\n[[File:Media-markt-automat.jpg|thumb|350px|Media Markt vending machine at Hamburg Airport, Germany]] \nMedia Markt had an aggressive advertising similar to American companies and also a few controversial commercials in 2000's. It is known in [[Germany]] for its humorous, but sometimes crude, [[advertising]] campaigns; for example, the slogan \"''Lasst euch nicht verarschen''\" meaning \"Don't let yourself be conned\", literally verbal prefix ''for-'' (ver-) + ass (Arsch) + infinitive suffix ''-en'' (-en).\n\nThe well-known advertising campaigns of the brands Media Markt and Saturn are designed by the internal marketing organization redblue Marketing GmbH in Munich .\n\n===Slogan===\n\nMedia Markt's main slogan \"''Ich bin doch nicht bl\u00f6d''\" (Hey, I'm not stupid) has been translated into the languages of the other countries where the company operates, except Italy and Poland:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Language || Slogan\n|-\n| [[German language|German]] || Ich bin doch nicht bl\u00f6d. (''I'm not stupid.'')\n|-\n| [[Spanish language|Spanish]] || \u00a1Yo no soy tonto! (''I am not a fool!'')\n|-\n| [[Dutch language|Dutch]] || Ik ben toch niet gek (''I'm not crazy'')\n|-\n| [[French language|French]] || Je ne suis pas fou. (''I'm not crazy'')\n|-\n| [[Galician language|Galician]] || Eu non son parvo! (''I am not a fool!'')\n|-\n| [[Greek language|Greek]] || \u0394\u03b5\u03bd \u03b5\u03af\u03bc\u03b1\u03b9 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03c7\u03c4\u03b5\u03c3\u03b9\u03bd\u03cc\u03c2! (''I was not born yesterday'')\n|-\n| [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]] || Mert h\u00fclye az\u00e9rt nem vagyok! (''Because I'm not stupid'')\n|-\n| [[Italian language|Italian]] || Non sono mica scemo! (''I am not stupid!''){{efn|This slogan is used in the Italophone Switzerland}}, Voglio il mondo (''I want the world'')\n|-\n| [[Polish language|Polish]] || Nieludzko niskie ceny. (''Inhumanly low prices.'')\n|-\n| [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] || Eu \u00e9 que n\u00e3o sou parvo! (''It's not me who's a fool!'')\n|-\n| [[Swedish language|Swedish]] || Allt annat k\u00e4nns puckat! (''Everything else seems stupid!'')\n|-\n| [[Catalan language|Catalan]] || Jo no s\u00f3c tonto! (''I am not stupid'')\n|-\n| [[Basque language|Basque]] || Ni ez naiz inozoa! (''I am not stupid'')\n|-\n| [[Turkish language|Turkish]] || Bakmadan Almam. (''I don't buy without looking.'')\n|-\n| [[Russian language|Russian]] || \u0414\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0439, \u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u0439 - \u0441\u0435\u0440\u0434\u0446\u0435\u043c \u0432\u044b\u0431\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0439! (''Go on, choose with your heart'')\n|}\n\n===2006 World Cup advertising campaign===\n\nPrior to the [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006 World Cup]], Media Markt launched a campaign, claiming to be the \"best fan supplier\" (\"''Bester Fanausr\u00fcster''\"), with commercials showing international football fans shopping at Media Markt, showing exaggerated stereotypes of the participating countries, and making fun of the [[Austria national football team|Austria]] team, which did  not qualify. This included a French seductress, Dutch fans smoking [[marijuana]] in caravans, or a Saudi haggling - to pay more. German fans were portrayed with big bellies, asking for refrigerators to keep their beer cool, rather than looking for a new TV set.\n\nAn additional series of ads, promoting a rebate of \u20ac10 for each goal Germany scores (except [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shoot-outs]]), showed international soccer fans begging the Germans to score as many goals as possible - against their own team.\n\nWhen the Netherlands lost to Portugal, Media Markt used a quote from a 1980s show featuring [[Rudi Carrell]], a Dutchman who was a long-time TV celebrity in Germany, to express ''[[Schadenfreude]]''. A [[FIFA World Cup Trophy|World Cup trophy]] is shown to grieving Dutch fans in their caravan with the comment \"This would have been your prize!\".\n\n===Polish advertising===\n[[File:Bydgoszcz Media Markt ulica Jagiello\u0144ska.jpg|thumb|350px|Media Markt store in Bydgoszcz, Poland]]\nIn March 2006, the \"Poland version\" showed moustache-wearing Polish customers praising the shop for \"prices deep like Polish soul\" before hugging the German sales managers, who looked quite uncomfortable in the bear hugs. Afterwards, one of the Germans pointed out that his watch was still there, and that \"The Pole is an honest person, after all\". Then, the three men are shown to be missing their trousers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEjOWqXAI7Y |title=Media Markt nie dla Polak\u00f3w |publisher=Youtube.com |date=31 March 2011}}</ref>\n\nThis commercial caused a scandal in Poland, for the widely known German stereotype of Poles being thieves. Media Markt argued that the advertisements also made fun of other national clich\u00e9s, including Germans, and none of the other clich\u00e9s were perceived as negative towards the people they presented. Its aim was to exaggerate the clich\u00e9 of the Polish thief to dismiss it as unjustified prejudice, Media Markt claimed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.focus.msn.de/finanzen/news/proteste-aus-polen_nid_26829.html |title=Proteste aus Polen - Media Markt zieht Fernseh-Werbung zur\u00fcck |publisher=Focus.msn.de |date=28 March 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060516121929/focus.msn.de/finanzen/news/proteste-aus-polen_nid_26829.html |archive-date=16 May 2006}}</ref>\n\nThe store apologised and withdrew the advert after their Polish branch asked to do so, following protests in Poland, a call from the Polish embassy in Berlin and protests from German [[Polish diaspora|Polonia]].\n\n===Portuguese advertising===\n\nIn January 2008 Media Markt launched a campaign presenting a fictitious country called \"Dumb Land\", where several characters with [[Eastern Europe]]an accents were presented as being from this country, which even has an anthem. A central theme of this campaign presented a [[Boy Scout]] as an idiot. This really upset people as many consider Scouts to be responsible and valued members of society. An online petition was created to persuade Media Markt to withdraw the campaign and to offer a public apology. Due to this petition and a lot of pressure from the Scouting movement, Media Markt had to remove the Boy Scout from their campaign, including TV and radio ads.\n\n===Turkish advertising===\n\nTurkish Union Association in [[Eski\u015fehir]], [[Turkey]] motivated suspension of an advertisement campaign by the group on grounds that Media Markt \"[[Article 301 (Turkish Penal Code)|insulted Turkishness]]\" by depicting consumers that purchased overpriced merchandise with animal heads. A ban of the advertisements lasted for 3 months in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100825185814/http://www.hurriyetdailynew.com/n.php?n=did-animals-really-insult-turkishness-2009-10-22 |title=Ads criticized for insulting Turkishness with animal heads on humans |publisher=Hurriyetdailynews.com |date=22 October 2009 |accessdate=2015-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100825185814/http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/n.php?n=did-animals-really-insult-turkishness-2009-10-22 |archive-date=25 August 2010}}</ref> There have been many accusations on their official Facebook fan page about their false product advertisements in Turkey.\n\n=== Saubillig ===\n\nA former German campaign played on the German expression \"saubillig\" which means extremely cheap, but literally \"sow (female pig) cheap\". ''Sau-'' is a common emphasising prefix in colloquial German. Inside the stores the entrances were signposted as \"Schweingang\" = wordplay on the word Eingang (Entrance) and Schwein (pig), and the exit as \"Sausgang\" = wordplay on the word Ausgang (Exit) and the German word for sow (Sau) - the female pig.\n\n== Controversies ==\n=== Misleading advertising methods ===\n==== Article without VAT ====\nMedia Markt promised in 2005 a promotion to sell items \"without [[VAT]]\" (with a discount equal to VAT). In fact, the prices for these items had previously been increased in order to actually achieve the normal price. A competitor sued a branch in Mannheim.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ftd.de/unternehmen/handel_dienstleister/129743.html |title=Media-Markt mogelte bei Mehrwertsteuer |publisher=ftd.de |date=8 November 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224021702/http://www.ftd.de/unternehmen/handel_dienstleister/129743.html |archive-date=24 February 2007}}</ref>\n\n==== Decoy offers ====\nThe MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group has made [[bait-and-switch]] in the past : articles were advertised extensively at extremely low prices, but were sold out within a very short time. According to case law on the law against unfair competition(UWG) advertised special offers must be available for at least two days. Consumer advocates criticized that this was often not guaranteed at Media Markt and Saturn. The group denied that; there were only a few exceptions despite large stocks. It is generally difficult to provide concrete evidence of such cases, since consumer protection groups do not have access to the delivery dates of the companies.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/lockvogel-angebote-gericht-knoepft-sich-media-markt-werbung-vor-a-481788.html |title=Gericht kn\u00f6pft sich Media-Markt-Werbung vor |publisher=spiegel.de |date=9 May 2007}}</ref>\n\n==== Price Guarantee  ====\nIn 2005, samples from the [[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]] in the Munich area showed that Media Markt or Saturn stores were more expensive in 15 out of 21 cases than local competitors. In Berlin they were 11 out of 21 cases. The MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group countered the allegations with a \"price guarantee\" that promised buyers a refund of the price difference if they found the product at a cheaper price in another shop.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.faz.net/aktuell/wirtschaft/unternehmen/einzelhandel-die-trickser-vom-media-markt-1303977.html |title=Die Trickser vom Media-Markt |publisher=faz.net |date=9 January 2006}}</ref>\n\n==== 0 -% - financing ====\nIn 2013, 0% financing from the Spanish bank [[Banco Santander]] was criticized. A credit loss insurance that costs 10% is taken out only on a note in the small print.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://helpv2.orf.at/stories/1714801/index.html |title=Kreditversicherung wider Willen |publisher=orf.at |date=23 March 2013}}</ref>\n\n=== The exclusive sale of Intel PCs ===\nAccording to research published by the [[Financial Times]] Germany in 2008, the MediaMarktSaturn Retail Group committed to [[Intel]] in 1999 to only sell PCs with Intel processors. The holding company received 85 million euros in purchase discounts and advertising grants from Intel in 2007 alone. The European antitrust authorities investigated the distortion of competition. Intel was fined 1.06 billion euros in May 2009 by the European Competition Commission for these and other antitrust violations.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/wettbewerbsverstoesse-intels-praktiken-schockieren-kartellrechtler-a-624575.html |title=Intels Praktiken schockieren Kartellrechtler |publisher=spiegel.de |date=13 May 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe retail chain was moved by Intel's discount system to have only insignificant or no computers with [[AMD]] processors in the range. According to the [[European Commission]], Intel has made direct and indirect payments to MSH since 1997. The payments were subject to the condition that, if possible, only offer Intel systems.\n\n=== Body searches ===\n\nIn 2014, in [[Krems an der Donau]] in [[Lower Austria]], theft of the Media Markt, which is said to have been committed by employees, not only carried out bag checks, as is common in many companies, but also body searches on all employees. The unions see this as a violation of [[human dignity]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noe.orf.at/v2/news/stories/2624102/ |title=Leibesvisitation bei Mitarbeitern |publisher=orf.at |date=7 January 2014}}</ref> As a consequence, employees of other branches in Austria reported this procedure. This approach was blamed on the security service providers by the company.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://noe.orf.at/v2/news/stories/2624466/ |title=Media Markt: Weitere Leibesvisitationen\n|publisher=orf.at |date=9 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== Antitrust proceedings ===\n\nOn June 13, 2014, the Austrian Federal Competition Authority (BWB) announced a decision by the cartel court on April 23, 2014 against Media-Saturn BeteiligungsgmbH. A fine of EUR 1,230,000 was imposed for vertical price matching of [[retail price]]s with the electronics industry between October 2009 and early 2013.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.bwb.gv.at/KartelleUndMarkmachtmissbrauch/Entscheidungen/Seiten/Media-Saturn.aspx |title=BWB/K-302 Geldbu\u00dfenentscheidung gegen Media-Saturn BeteiligungsgmbH\n|publisher=bwb.gv.at |date=13 June 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140928050906/http://www.bwb.gv.at/KartelleUndMarkmachtmissbrauch/Entscheidungen/Seiten/Media-Saturn.aspx |archive-date=28 September 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Media Markt}}\n* {{official|http://www.mediamarkt.com/ }}\n\n[[Category:Retail companies established in 1979]]\n[[Category:Consumer electronics retailers of Germany]]\n[[Category:Retail companies of Germany]]\n[[Category:Metro Group]]\n[[Category:Scandals in Poland]]\n", "name_user": "Daniel.9", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MediaMarkt"}
{"title_page": "Tamang people", "text_new": "{{copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{infobox ethnic group\n| group = Tamang/ moormi\n| image = \n| flag  = \n| caption =  \n| population = \n| popplace = [[Nepal]], [[India]] ([[Sikkim]], [[West Bengal]])\n| langs = [[Tamang language|Tamang]], [[Nepali language|Nepali]]\n| religions = \n| related = [[Uighur]], [[Hui]], [[Tibetan]]\n}}\nThe '''Tamang''' {{bo-textonly|\u0f4f\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f44}} ([[Devanagari]]: \u0924\u093e\u092e\u093e\u0919; ''t\u0101m\u0101ng'') are the largest ethnic group of [[Tibetans ]] who lived in nepal. Tamangs constitute 5.6% of the Nepalese population at over 1.3 million in 2001, increasing to 1,539,830 as of 2011 census,<ref name=\"Ghimire\">{{cite web |url=https://publications.theseus.fi/bitstream/handle/10024/73036/Ghimire_Mahesh.pdf?sequence=1 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-12-22 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082038/https://publications.theseus.fi/bitstream/handle/10024/73036/Ghimire_Mahesh.pdf?sequence=1 |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref> yet contested. [[Nepali Gorkha|Nepali Tamangs]] are also a significant number in [[Sikkim]] and [[Darjeeling District]] of [[West Bengal]], [[India]] as permanent settlers;<ref name=\"EmergentNE\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427035600/https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|archivedate=2016-04-27|url-status=live|accessdate=2015-12-23}} Emergent North-East : A Way Forward By H. C. Sadangi</ref> their languages are the fifth most spoken in Nepal (note all Tamang languages are not mutually intelligible). They are considered as one of the indigenous people of Nepal and India.<ref name=\n\"nefin\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nefin.org.np/hppics/10789_Nepal%20Tamang%20Ghedung%20Kabhre,%20Report%20on%20Socio-Economic%20Status%20of%20Tamang-%20Kavre.doc |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130312053215/http://www.nefin.org.np//hppics/10789_Nepal%20Tamang%20Ghedung%20Kabhre,%20Report%20on%20Socio-Economic%20Status%20of%20Tamang-%20Kavre.doc |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-03-12 |title=Report on Socio-Economic Status of Tamang\u2013Kavre |publisher=Nefin.org.np |accessdate=2015-12-23 }}</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\n''Tamang'' was derived from the word ''Tamag'', where ''Ta'' means \u201chorse\u201d, and ''Mag'' means \u201csoldier\u201d in tibetan language or The tibetan soldier who live in nepal and they descendants of tibet but no such evidence have been found nor they posess the horse riding skill of war <ref name=\"Chronicles of ADVENTURE TRAVEL\">{{Cite news|url=https://advancedadventures.wordpress.com/2015/01/05/tamang-people-of-nepal/|title=Who actually are the Tamang People? An Insight into Indigenous Tribe of Nepal|date=2015-01-05|work=Chronicles of ADVENTURE TRAVEL|access-date=2018-02-28|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180301044744/https://advancedadventures.wordpress.com/2015/01/05/tamang-people-of-nepal/|archive-date=2018-03-01|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Status ==\n{{quotebox|width=25em| bgcolor=#B0C4DE|align=left|1/3 of all deaths were among Tamang people, and roughly 2/3 of the 600,000 structures completely destroyed were in Tamang dominant areas.<ref name=\"nepalitimes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nepalitimes.com/blogs/thebrief/2015/07/05/the-tamang-epicentre/ |title=The Brief \u00bb Blog Archive \u00bb The Tamang epicentre |publisher=Nepali Times |date=2015-07-05 |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128211844/http://www.nepalitimes.com/blogs/thebrief/2015/07/05/the-tamang-epicentre/ |archivedate=2015-11-28 }}</ref> It is the poverty, neglect and outright discrimination in Nepal against Tamangs that makes them even more vulnerable to disasters like earthquakes, landslides and floods&mdash;Anthropologist Mukta Singh Lama.<ref name=\"nepalitimes\"/>}}\n\n==Political participation==\n{{Multiple issues|{{Essay-like|date=January 2019}}{{POV section|date=January 2019}}}}\nTamangs are represented by Tamsaling Rastriya Mukti Morcha and [[Tamsaling Nepal Rastriya Dal]]. The umbrella group [[Mongol National Organisation]] supports self-determination and works against said discrimination not just for Tamangs but for all groups in Nepal. The MNO is against conversion to Hinduism of non-Hindus. It currently holds no official parliamentary vote. The [[Federal Limbuwan State Council]] (FLSC) also works towards similar goals for [[self-determination]] for the [[Kirati people]]s, who co-mingle with Tamangs, citing a reneged treaty with Kathmandu for autonomy.<ref>Chemjong, Iman Singh (2003). History and Culture of Kirat People (4th ed.). Kathmandu: Kirat Yakthung Chumlung. {{ISBN|99933-809-1-1}}.</ref>  The associated [[Sanghiya Limbuwan Party]] has participated in calling [[bandh|banda]] during the [[2015 Nepal blockade]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/sanghiya-limbuwan-party-calls-indefinite-eastern-region-bandh/ |title=Sanghiya Limbuwan Party calls indefinite Eastern Region bandh |publisher=The Himalayan Times |date=2015-09-04 |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151223090948/http://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/sanghiya-limbuwan-party-calls-indefinite-eastern-region-bandh/ |archivedate=2015-12-23 }}</ref> nevertheless international press had not only failed to take note of their ''bandh'', but even pretended not to notice their very existence and instead focused intently on 4 party India-backed Madhesi Morcha actions, geopolitical concerns with [[China]], as [[Limbuwan]] also opposes both the Madhesi goals as well as Kathmandu's domination.<ref>{{cite web |author=Om Astha Rai |url=http://nepalitimes.com/regular-columns/As-It-Happens/Nepal-needs-to-look-within-and-mend-fences,603 |title=Look south &#124; As It Happens |publisher=Nepali Times |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151223143548/http://nepalitimes.com/regular-columns/As-It-Happens/Nepal-needs-to-look-within-and-mend-fences,603 |archivedate=2015-12-23 }}</ref>  However, there is rationale to India and Western nation's denial of information about Limbuwan actions during the fuel blockade, in the 1980s, a violent [[Gorkhaland]] movement within [[India]] was led by the prominent Tamang [[Subhas Ghising]] to which India had viewed as a security threat due to the proximity of the [[Siliguri Corridor]].<ref name=\"EmergentNE\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427035600/https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|archivedate=2016-04-27|url-status=live|accessdate=2015-12-23}} Emergent North-East : A Way Forward By H. C. Sadangi</ref> [[Madan Tamang]], a Tamang-Indian politician, and proponent for Gorkhaland statehood, was assassinated in 2010, with [[West Bengal]] government placing blame on another Gorkhaland political party, in effect weakening the movement. [[Gorkhaland Territorial Administration]] was then created in place of statehood in [[India]], nevertheless across the border, ethnic discrimination issues regarding the numerous groups (who have taken part in each other's politics) are left unresolved within Nepal. In 2017 [[Binay Tamang]] was appointed as the Chairperson of GTA.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/gta-reconstituted-rebel-gjm-leader-tamang-is-chairperson/article19724174.ece|title=GTA reconstituted, rebel GJM leader Tamang is chairperson|date=2017-09-21|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-02-28|others=Special Correspondent, Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180228230723/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/gta-reconstituted-rebel-gjm-leader-tamang-is-chairperson/article19724174.ece|archivedate=2018-02-28}}</ref>\n\n==Culture==\n\n\nTamang are very rich in their tradition and culture. They have their own language, culture, dress and social structure. They have over 100 sub-clans. Tamang believe in Buddhism, and famously said that 90 percent of Tamang follow Buddhism as their religion. Their language comes from Tibeto-Burman language family. They follow the Chinese lunar calendar of the 12-year cycle and their typical song-dance which is famously known as Tamang selo, which include the songs of humor and wit, satire, joy and sorrow. Tamangs have their own music. Their musical instrument is called Damphu (a small round drum covered with goat skin). Loshar is their religious festival.[https://www.indigenousvoice.com/en/indigenous-peoples/18/tamang.html]\n\n===Festivals===\n[[File:Tamang Sonam Lochhar 2018 DC (38533764940).jpg|thumb|Sonam Lochar Festival]]\n'''Sonam Lhochhar'''  is the main festival of the Tamangs and is celebrated in the month on Magh (February - March).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://streetnepal.com/sonam-lhochhar-celebrated/|title=Sonam Lhochhar celebrated  {{!}} Street Nepal|website=streetnepal.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-28|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816080424/http://streetnepal.com/sonam-lhochhar-celebrated/|archivedate=2016-08-16}}</ref> It is celebrated to welcome the Tamang new year.\n\nColorful flags, printed Buddhist [[mantra]] cloths are put up in various places in villages and towns.<ref name=\"Ghimire\" />  The Tamangs have a genre of music called \" ''[[Tamang Selo]]\"'' that is performed with the ''[[Damphu drum|Damplu]]'' instrument, also known as Damphoo Dance, having a brisk movement and rhythmic beat specific to the Tamangs.<ref name=\"EmergentNE\" />\n\nThe second most important festival is '''Saga Dawa''' (Buddha Jayanti) and is celebrated as a religious festival.<ref name=\"Chronicles of ADVENTURE TRAVEL\"/>\n\n[[Dashain]] and [[Tihar (festival)]] is also celebrated with much enthusiasm by Tamangs.<ref name=\"Ghimire\" />\n\n===Livelihood===\nMost Tamangs are farmers, engaged in [[agriculture]]. Due to the lack of irrigation at higher altitudes, their crops are often limited to corn, millet, wheat, barley, and potatoes.  They often supplement their farming income with manual labour.  Due to the discrimination experienced by the Tamang people in the past, they have remained on the whole poorly educated, and the majority have been limited to working as farmers, mountain trekking, portering, and driving in Kathmandu. They also work in manufacture of Tibetan rugs, Thankas (Tibetan painting), driving and labour.  As far as farming is concerned, Tamang are dependent on rainfall and do not employ modern machinery.<ref name=\"Ghimire\" />\n\n==Trekking and tourism==\nTamang villages are often visited on Nepal's numerous trekking routes, one being labelled ''Tamang Heritage Trail''.<ref>{{cite web |author=Post Report |url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2015-07-30/tamang-heritage-trail-reopens-after-quake.html |title=The Kathmandu Post :: Tamang Heritage Trail reopens after quake |publisher=Kathmandupost.ekantipur.com |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208065012/http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2015-07-30/tamang-heritage-trail-reopens-after-quake.html |archivedate=2015-12-08 }}</ref>\n== Notable Tamangs ==\n[[File:Navneet-Aditya-Waiba-Live.jpg|thumb|Navneet Aditya Waiba- Nepali Folk Singer|alt=Nepali Folk Singer]]\n[[File:Kulman-Ghising-Nepal-Electricity-Authority MD.jpg|thumb|Kulman Ghising]]\n\nTamangs are known in Nepali Art/Music, Politics, Novels and Civil servants of Nepal. Some prominent names are:\n* [[Hira Devi Waiba]], singer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1110120/jsp/siliguri/story_13466851.jsp|title=The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) {{!}} North Bengal & Sikkim  {{!}} Hira Devi dies of burn injuries|website=www.telegraphindia.com|access-date=2018-03-11}}</ref>\n* [[Kunti Moktan]], singer<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dhakatopi.com/kunti-moktan|title=Kunti Moktan|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Navneet Aditya Waiba]]\n* [[Phiroj Shyangden]]\n* [[Raju Lama]]\n* [[Parijat (writer)]]\n* [[Prashant Tamang]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/2017/06/21/indian-idol-winner-prashant-tamang-is-the-rallying-voice-of-the_a_22494541/|title=Indian Idol Winner Prashant Tamang Is The Rallying Voice Of The Gorkhaland Protests|date=2017-06-21|work=Huffington Post India|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en-IN}}</ref>\n* [[Zenisha Moktan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nepaliactress.com/tag/zenisha-moktan/|title=Zenisha Moktan {{!}} Nepali Actress|website=nepaliactress.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-11}}</ref>\n* [[Nima Rumba]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.myrepublica.com/archive/29310/Nima-Rumba-&-Style|title=Nima Rumba & Style|work=My Republica|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Aruna Lama]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bossnepal.com/melody-queen-aruna-lama/|title=Melody queen Aruna Lama|work=Boss Nepal|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n* [[Karma Yonzon]]\n* [[Gopal Yonjan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hamrokalakar.com/gopal-yonzon|title=Gopal Yonzon Biography {{!}} Hamro Kalakar|last=Kalakar|first=Hamro|website=www.hamrokalakar.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-11}}</ref>\n* [[Kul Man Ghising]]\n* [[Dil_Bahadur_Lama|DB Lama]]\n* [[Vijaya Lama]]\n*[[Robin Tamang]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Tamang language]]\n* [[Tamang Selo]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.everestnews.com/stories004sec4002/everesttamangs11263002one.htm|title=Introduction to Ethnic Groups &ndash; The Tamangs: The Unknown Mount Everest Climbers|website= EverestNews.com|accessdate=4 January 2013}}\n\n{{Ethnic groups in Nepal}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Buddhist communities of India]]\n[[Category:Buddhist communities of Nepal]]\n[[Category:Sino-Tibetan-speaking people]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Northeast India]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in South Asia]]\n", "text_old": "{{copy edit|date=April 2020}}\n{{refimprove|date=March 2020}}\n\n{{infobox ethnic group\n| group = Tamang/ moormi\n| image = \n| flag  = \n| caption =  \n| population = \n| popplace = [[Nepal]], [[India]] ([[Sikkim]], [[West Bengal]])\n| langs = [[Tamang language|Tamang]], [[Nepali language|Nepali]]\n| religions = \n| related = [[Uighur]] [[hui]  [[Tibetan]]\n}}\nThe '''Tamang''' {{bo-textonly|\u0f4f\u0f0b\u0f58\u0f44}} ([[Devanagari]]: \u0924\u093e\u092e\u093e\u0919; ''t\u0101m\u0101ng'') are the largest ethnic group of [[Tibetans ]] who lived in nepal. Tamangs constitute 5.6% of the Nepalese population at over 1.3 million in 2001, increasing to 1,539,830 as of 2011 census,<ref name=\"Ghimire\">{{cite web |url=https://publications.theseus.fi/bitstream/handle/10024/73036/Ghimire_Mahesh.pdf?sequence=1 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-12-22 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304082038/https://publications.theseus.fi/bitstream/handle/10024/73036/Ghimire_Mahesh.pdf?sequence=1 |archivedate=2016-03-04 }}</ref> yet contested. [[Nepali Gorkha|Nepali Tamangs]] are also a significant number in [[Sikkim]] and [[Darjeeling District]] of [[West Bengal]], [[India]] as permanent settlers;<ref name=\"EmergentNE\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427035600/https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|archivedate=2016-04-27|url-status=live|accessdate=2015-12-23}} Emergent North-East : A Way Forward By H. C. Sadangi</ref> their languages are the fifth most spoken in Nepal (note all Tamang languages are not mutually intelligible). They are considered as one of the indigenous people of Nepal and India.<ref name=\n\"nefin\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nefin.org.np/hppics/10789_Nepal%20Tamang%20Ghedung%20Kabhre,%20Report%20on%20Socio-Economic%20Status%20of%20Tamang-%20Kavre.doc |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130312053215/http://www.nefin.org.np//hppics/10789_Nepal%20Tamang%20Ghedung%20Kabhre,%20Report%20on%20Socio-Economic%20Status%20of%20Tamang-%20Kavre.doc |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-03-12 |title=Report on Socio-Economic Status of Tamang\u2013Kavre |publisher=Nefin.org.np |accessdate=2015-12-23 }}</ref>\n==Etymology==\n''Tamang'' was derived from the word ''Tamag'', where ''Ta'' means \u201chorse\u201d, and ''Mag'' means \u201csoldier\u201d in tibetan language or The tibetan soldier who live in nepal and they descendants of tibet but no such evidence have been found nor they posess the horse riding skill of war <ref name=\"Chronicles of ADVENTURE TRAVEL\">{{Cite news|url=https://advancedadventures.wordpress.com/2015/01/05/tamang-people-of-nepal/|title=Who actually are the Tamang People? An Insight into Indigenous Tribe of Nepal|date=2015-01-05|work=Chronicles of ADVENTURE TRAVEL|access-date=2018-02-28|language=en-US|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180301044744/https://advancedadventures.wordpress.com/2015/01/05/tamang-people-of-nepal/|archive-date=2018-03-01|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Status ==\n{{quotebox|width=25em| bgcolor=#B0C4DE|align=left|1/3 of all deaths were among Tamang people, and roughly 2/3 of the 600,000 structures completely destroyed were in Tamang dominant areas.<ref name=\"nepalitimes\">{{cite web |url=http://www.nepalitimes.com/blogs/thebrief/2015/07/05/the-tamang-epicentre/ |title=The Brief \u00bb Blog Archive \u00bb The Tamang epicentre |publisher=Nepali Times |date=2015-07-05 |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151128211844/http://www.nepalitimes.com/blogs/thebrief/2015/07/05/the-tamang-epicentre/ |archivedate=2015-11-28 }}</ref> It is the poverty, neglect and outright discrimination in Nepal against Tamangs that makes them even more vulnerable to disasters like earthquakes, landslides and floods&mdash;Anthropologist Mukta Singh Lama.<ref name=\"nepalitimes\"/>}}\n\n==Political participation==\n{{Multiple issues|{{Essay-like|date=January 2019}}{{POV section|date=January 2019}}}}\nTamangs are represented by Tamsaling Rastriya Mukti Morcha and [[Tamsaling Nepal Rastriya Dal]]. The umbrella group [[Mongol National Organisation]] supports self-determination and works against said discrimination not just for Tamangs but for all groups in Nepal. The MNO is against conversion to Hinduism of non-Hindus. It currently holds no official parliamentary vote. The [[Federal Limbuwan State Council]] (FLSC) also works towards similar goals for [[self-determination]] for the [[Kirati people]]s, who co-mingle with Tamangs, citing a reneged treaty with Kathmandu for autonomy.<ref>Chemjong, Iman Singh (2003). History and Culture of Kirat People (4th ed.). Kathmandu: Kirat Yakthung Chumlung. {{ISBN|99933-809-1-1}}.</ref>  The associated [[Sanghiya Limbuwan Party]] has participated in calling [[bandh|banda]] during the [[2015 Nepal blockade]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/sanghiya-limbuwan-party-calls-indefinite-eastern-region-bandh/ |title=Sanghiya Limbuwan Party calls indefinite Eastern Region bandh |publisher=The Himalayan Times |date=2015-09-04 |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151223090948/http://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/sanghiya-limbuwan-party-calls-indefinite-eastern-region-bandh/ |archivedate=2015-12-23 }}</ref> nevertheless international press had not only failed to take note of their ''bandh'', but even pretended not to notice their very existence and instead focused intently on 4 party India-backed Madhesi Morcha actions, geopolitical concerns with [[China]], as [[Limbuwan]] also opposes both the Madhesi goals as well as Kathmandu's domination.<ref>{{cite web |author=Om Astha Rai |url=http://nepalitimes.com/regular-columns/As-It-Happens/Nepal-needs-to-look-within-and-mend-fences,603 |title=Look south &#124; As It Happens |publisher=Nepali Times |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151223143548/http://nepalitimes.com/regular-columns/As-It-Happens/Nepal-needs-to-look-within-and-mend-fences,603 |archivedate=2015-12-23 }}</ref>  However, there is rationale to India and Western nation's denial of information about Limbuwan actions during the fuel blockade, in the 1980s, a violent [[Gorkhaland]] movement within [[India]] was led by the prominent Tamang [[Subhas Ghising]] to which India had viewed as a security threat due to the proximity of the [[Siliguri Corridor]].<ref name=\"EmergentNE\">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|title=Archived copy|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160427035600/https://books.google.com/books?id=uLfE8HGwdIMC&pg=PA277|archivedate=2016-04-27|url-status=live|accessdate=2015-12-23}} Emergent North-East : A Way Forward By H. C. Sadangi</ref> [[Madan Tamang]], a Tamang-Indian politician, and proponent for Gorkhaland statehood, was assassinated in 2010, with [[West Bengal]] government placing blame on another Gorkhaland political party, in effect weakening the movement. [[Gorkhaland Territorial Administration]] was then created in place of statehood in [[India]], nevertheless across the border, ethnic discrimination issues regarding the numerous groups (who have taken part in each other's politics) are left unresolved within Nepal. In 2017 [[Binay Tamang]] was appointed as the Chairperson of GTA.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/gta-reconstituted-rebel-gjm-leader-tamang-is-chairperson/article19724174.ece|title=GTA reconstituted, rebel GJM leader Tamang is chairperson|date=2017-09-21|work=The Hindu|access-date=2018-02-28|others=Special Correspondent, Special Correspondent|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180228230723/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/gta-reconstituted-rebel-gjm-leader-tamang-is-chairperson/article19724174.ece|archivedate=2018-02-28}}</ref>\n\n==Culture==\n\n\nTamang are very rich in their tradition and culture. They have their own language, culture, dress and social structure. They have over 100 sub-clans. Tamang believe in Buddhism, and famously said that 90 percent of Tamang follow Buddhism as their religion. Their language comes from Tibeto-Burman language family. They follow the Chinese lunar calendar of the 12-year cycle and their typical song-dance which is famously known as Tamang selo, which include the songs of humor and wit, satire, joy and sorrow. Tamangs have their own music. Their musical instrument is called Damphu (a small round drum covered with goat skin). Loshar is their religious festival.[https://www.indigenousvoice.com/en/indigenous-peoples/18/tamang.html]\n\n===Festivals===\n[[File:Tamang Sonam Lochhar 2018 DC (38533764940).jpg|thumb|Sonam Lochar Festival]]\n'''Sonam Lhochhar'''  is the main festival of the Tamangs and is celebrated in the month on Magh (February - March).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://streetnepal.com/sonam-lhochhar-celebrated/|title=Sonam Lhochhar celebrated  {{!}} Street Nepal|website=streetnepal.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-02-28|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160816080424/http://streetnepal.com/sonam-lhochhar-celebrated/|archivedate=2016-08-16}}</ref> It is celebrated to welcome the Tamang new year.\n\nColorful flags, printed Buddhist [[mantra]] cloths are put up in various places in villages and towns.<ref name=\"Ghimire\" />  The Tamangs have a genre of music called \" ''[[Tamang Selo]]\"'' that is performed with the ''[[Damphu drum|Damplu]]'' instrument, also known as Damphoo Dance, having a brisk movement and rhythmic beat specific to the Tamangs.<ref name=\"EmergentNE\" />\n\nThe second most important festival is '''Saga Dawa''' (Buddha Jayanti) and is celebrated as a religious festival.<ref name=\"Chronicles of ADVENTURE TRAVEL\"/>\n\n[[Dashain]] and [[Tihar (festival)]] is also celebrated with much enthusiasm by Tamangs.<ref name=\"Ghimire\" />\n\n===Livelihood===\nMost Tamangs are farmers, engaged in [[agriculture]]. Due to the lack of irrigation at higher altitudes, their crops are often limited to corn, millet, wheat, barley, and potatoes.  They often supplement their farming income with manual labour.  Due to the discrimination experienced by the Tamang people in the past, they have remained on the whole poorly educated, and the majority have been limited to working as farmers, mountain trekking, portering, and driving in Kathmandu. They also work in manufacture of Tibetan rugs, Thankas (Tibetan painting), driving and labour.  As far as farming is concerned, Tamang are dependent on rainfall and do not employ modern machinery.<ref name=\"Ghimire\" />\n\n==Trekking and tourism==\nTamang villages are often visited on Nepal's numerous trekking routes, one being labelled ''Tamang Heritage Trail''.<ref>{{cite web |author=Post Report |url=http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2015-07-30/tamang-heritage-trail-reopens-after-quake.html |title=The Kathmandu Post :: Tamang Heritage Trail reopens after quake |publisher=Kathmandupost.ekantipur.com |accessdate=2015-12-23 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208065012/http://kathmandupost.ekantipur.com/printedition/news/2015-07-30/tamang-heritage-trail-reopens-after-quake.html |archivedate=2015-12-08 }}</ref>\n== Notable Tamangs ==\n[[File:Navneet-Aditya-Waiba-Live.jpg|thumb|Navneet Aditya Waiba- Nepali Folk Singer|alt=Nepali Folk Singer]]\n[[File:Kulman-Ghising-Nepal-Electricity-Authority MD.jpg|thumb|Kulman Ghising]]\n\nTamangs are known in Nepali Art/Music, Politics, Novels and Civil servants of Nepal. Some prominent names are:\n* [[Hira Devi Waiba]], singer<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/1110120/jsp/siliguri/story_13466851.jsp|title=The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) {{!}} North Bengal & Sikkim  {{!}} Hira Devi dies of burn injuries|website=www.telegraphindia.com|access-date=2018-03-11}}</ref>\n* [[Kunti Moktan]], singer<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://dhakatopi.com/kunti-moktan|title=Kunti Moktan|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Navneet Aditya Waiba]]\n* [[Phiroj Shyangden]]\n* [[Raju Lama]]\n* [[Parijat (writer)]]\n* [[Prashant Tamang]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.in/2017/06/21/indian-idol-winner-prashant-tamang-is-the-rallying-voice-of-the_a_22494541/|title=Indian Idol Winner Prashant Tamang Is The Rallying Voice Of The Gorkhaland Protests|date=2017-06-21|work=Huffington Post India|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en-IN}}</ref>\n* [[Zenisha Moktan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nepaliactress.com/tag/zenisha-moktan/|title=Zenisha Moktan {{!}} Nepali Actress|website=nepaliactress.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-11}}</ref>\n* [[Nima Rumba]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.myrepublica.com/archive/29310/Nima-Rumba-&-Style|title=Nima Rumba & Style|work=My Republica|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[Aruna Lama]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bossnepal.com/melody-queen-aruna-lama/|title=Melody queen Aruna Lama|work=Boss Nepal|access-date=2018-03-11|language=en-US}}</ref>\n* [[Karma Yonzon]]\n* [[Gopal Yonjan]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hamrokalakar.com/gopal-yonzon|title=Gopal Yonzon Biography {{!}} Hamro Kalakar|last=Kalakar|first=Hamro|website=www.hamrokalakar.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-03-11}}</ref>\n* [[Kul Man Ghising]]\n* [[Dil_Bahadur_Lama|DB Lama]]\n* [[Vijaya Lama]]\n*[[Robin Tamang]]\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Tamang language]]\n* [[Tamang Selo]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.everestnews.com/stories004sec4002/everesttamangs11263002one.htm|title=Introduction to Ethnic Groups &ndash; The Tamangs: The Unknown Mount Everest Climbers|website= EverestNews.com|accessdate=4 January 2013}}\n\n{{Ethnic groups in Nepal}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Buddhist communities of India]]\n[[Category:Buddhist communities of Nepal]]\n[[Category:Sino-Tibetan-speaking people]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Nepal]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Northeast India]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in South Asia]]\n", "name_user": "Miniapolis", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Fixes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tamang_people"}
{"title_page": "Cinderella (2015 Disney film)", "text_new": "{{For|the unrelated Indian film|Cinderella (2015 Indian film)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox film \n|name           = Cinderella\n|image          = Cinderella 2015 official poster.jpg\n|caption        = Theatrical release poster\n|director       = [[Kenneth Branagh]]\n|producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Simon Kinberg]]\n* [[Allison Shearmur]]\n* [[David Barron (film producer)|David Barron]]\n}}\n|screenplay     = [[Chris Weitz]]\n|based on       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Walt Disney Animation Studios|Disney's]] ''[[Cinderella (1950 film)|Cinderella]]''<ref name=PressKit/>\n*''[[Cinderella|Cendrillon]]'' by [[Charles Perrault]]}}\n|starring       = {{Plainlist|  <!--DO NOT CHANGE. PER OFFICIAL BILLING BLOCK-->\n* [[Lily James]]\n* [[Cate Blanchett]]\n* [[Richard Madden]]\n* [[Stellan Skarsg\u00e5rd]]\n* [[Holliday Grainger]]\n* [[Sophie McShera]]\n* [[Derek Jacobi]]\n* [[Helena Bonham Carter]]\n}}\n|music          = [[Patrick Doyle]]\n|cinematography = [[Haris Zambarloukos]]\n|editing        = [[Martin Walsh (film editor)|Martin Walsh]]\n|studio         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Walt Disney Pictures]]\n* [[Genre Films|Kinberg Genre]]\n* Allison Shearmur Productions\n* [[Beagle Pug Films]]}}\n|distributor    = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Walt Disney Studios<br />Motion Pictures]]\n|released       = {{Film date|2015|2|13|[[65th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin]]|2015|3|13|United States|2015|3|27|United Kingdom}}\n|runtime        = 106 minutes<ref name=\"BBFC\">{{cite web|title= ''Cinderella'' (U)|url= https://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/cinderella-2014|publisher = [[British Board of Film Classification]]|accessdate = March 21, 2015}}</ref>\n|country        = {{unbulleted list|United States<ref name=\"BFI\">{{cite web |title=Cinderella (2015) {{!}} BFI |url=http://www.bfi.org.uk/films-tv-people/54c821a2806ec |website=[[British Film Institute|BFI]] |accessdate=June 24, 2018 |language=en}}</ref>|United Kingdom<ref name=\"lum\">{{cite web |title=LUMIERE : Film: Cinderella |url=http://lumiere.obs.coe.int/web/film_info/?id=55121 |website=[[LUMIERE]] |accessdate=June 24, 2018}}</ref>}}<!--COUNTRY OF NATIONAL ORIGIN ONLY-->\n|language       = English\n|budget         = $95\u2013100 million<ref name=BOM/><ref name=\"filmla\">{{cite web|url=https://www.filmla.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/2015_film_study_v5_WEB.pdf|title=2015 Feature Film Study|work=FilmL.A.|format=pdf|page=21|accessdate=May 12, 2018}}</ref>\n|gross          = $542.4 million<ref name=\"BOM\">{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=cinderella2015.htm|title=Cinderella (2015)|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=May 22, 2016}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Cinderella''''' is a 2015 [[romantic fantasy film]] directed by [[Kenneth Branagh]], with a screenplay written by [[Chris Weitz]], and co-produced by [[Walt Disney Pictures]], [[Genre Films|Kinberg Genre]], [[Allison Shearmur|Allison Shearmur Productions]], and [[Beagle Pug Films]]. The film is based on the [[Cinderella|eponymous folk tale]] and is a [[live action]] adaptation of [[Walt Disney]]'s [[Cinderella (1950 film)|1950 animated film of the same name]].<ref name=PressKit>{{cite web|title=Cinderella: Press Release|url=http://www.wdsmediafile.com/media/Cinderella/writen-material/Cinderella54dc0b6c538d2.pdf|website=The Walt Disney Company|publisher=The Walt Disney Studios|accessdate=February 13, 2015}}</ref> It features [[Lily James]] as the [[Cinderella (Disney character)|eponymous character]], with [[Cate Blanchett]], [[Richard Madden]], [[Stellan Skarsg\u00e5rd]], [[Holliday Grainger]], [[Sophie McShera]], [[Derek Jacobi]], and [[Helena Bonham Carter]].\n\nDevelopment for a [[List of Disney live-action remakes of animated films|live-action reimagining]] of the original animated film began in May 2010, with producer [[Simon Kinberg]] attached to the project. In late January 2013, Branagh signed on to direct, with Weitz hired to revise a script from [[Aline Brosh McKenna]]. In November 2012, casting began with Blanchett being the first to sign on; James was eventually cast in the titular role in April 2013. [[Principal photography]] began at [[Pinewood Studios]] in [[Buckinghamshire, England]] on September 23, 2013, and ended on December 14.\n\n''Cinderella'' had its world premiere on February 13, 2015, at the [[65th Berlin International Film Festival]] and was released theatrically in the United States on March 13, 2015, and in the United Kingdom on March 27 in standard and [[IMAX]] formats by [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures]]. It grossed over $542&nbsp;million worldwide, becoming Branagh's highest-grossing film to date as a director. The film received generally  positive reviews from critics, with many praising the performances (particularly James, Blanchett, and Bonham Carter), Branagh's direction, musical score, costume design, production values, and faithfulness to the original animated film. It received a nomination at the [[88th Academy Awards]], [[21st Critics' Choice Awards]] and [[69th British Academy Film Awards]], all for costume design. \n\n{{TOC limit|3}}\n\n==Plot==\nElla and her parents live a humble but happy life until her mother falls ill. Ella promises to follow her mother's dying wish: to have courage and be kind. Years later, Ella's father marries Lady Tremaine, who has two unpleasant daughters, Drisella and Anastasia. Ella's father leaves on business, and Lady Tremaine reveals her cruel and jealous nature, pushing Ella to give up her bedroom to the stepsisters and move to the attic. When Ella's father unexpectedly dies, Lady Tremaine dismisses the household staff to save money and forces all their chores on Ella. Seeing Ella's face covered in [[cinders]] after sleeping by the fireplace, her step-family mockingly dubs her \"Cinderella\".\n\nDistraught, Ella rides off into the woods where she happens to encounter Kit, the [[crown prince]], hunting. He hides that he is a prince and instead introduces himself as a palace apprentice. Ella and Kit take a liking to each other, but they part without him learning her name. The King discovers he has little time left to live, and urges Kit to take a princess as his bride at the upcoming royal ball. Kit persuades his father to also invite every eligible maiden in the kingdom, hoping to see Ella again.\n\nOn the night of the ball, Ella tries to join her step-family, wearing her mother\u2019s old gown that she has refashioned, but Lady Tremaine and Drisella tear it to shreds and leave without her. Ella runs into the garden in tears and meets an old beggar woman, who reveals herself to be Ella's Fairy Godmother. She magically transforms a pumpkin into a carriage, mice into horses, lizards into footmen, and a goose into the coachman. She then transforms Ella's ripped gown into a beautiful ballgown, complete with a pair of glass slippers. As Ella departs, the Fairy Godmother warns her the spell will end at the last stroke of midnight, and casts a final spell to prevent Ella's stepfamily from recognizing her.\n\nAt the ball, the entire court is entranced by Ella. She dances with Kit, much to the chagrin of the Grand Duke who has already promised Kit to Princess Chelina of Zaragoza, which Lady Tremaine overhears. Though surprised at Kit's true identity, Ella and the prince bond. Before Ella can tell Kit her name, the clock chimes midnight and she flees the palace, losing one of her slippers. Pursued by the Grand Duke and his men, Ella manages to escape home before the final stroke of midnight; the spell dissipates and everything reverts back to its true form. Ella hides the remaining slipper under her bedroom floorboards.\n\nThe King dies, but not before giving his son permission to marry Ella. Now King, Kit issues a royal proclamation professing his love for the \u201cmystery princess\u201d and requests she present herself. Ella hurries to retrieve the glass slipper to prove her identity, only to find it with her stepmother. Having deduced that Ella is the mystery princess, Lady Tremaine attempts to blackmail Ella to make her head of the royal household and find respectable husbands for her stepsisters, in exchange for giving Ella's hand in marriage to Kit. Ella refuses, and Lady Tremaine smashes the slipper and locks Ella in the attic. She brings the shattered remains of the slipper to the Grand Duke, who agrees to make her a [[countess]] and secure marriages for her daughters in exchange for keeping Ella hidden.\n\nThe Grand Duke and the Captain of the guards lead the search for the mystery princess by trying the slipper on every woman in the kingdom, but it refuses to fit anyone. At the Tremaine estate, the shoe fits neither stepsister; the company prepares to depart, but hear Ella singing ''[[Lavender's Blue]]''. The Grand Duke urges them to leave, but Kit, who has secretly accompanied them, commands the Captain to investigate. The slipper fits Ella, and she and Kit promise to accept one another for who they truly are. As they leave, Ella forgives her stepmother. Soon after, Lady Tremaine, her daughters, and the Grand Duke leave the kingdom, never to return.\n\nElla and Kit marry and become the kingdom's most beloved monarchs, ruling with the same courage and kindness that Ella had promised her mother, and live happily ever after.\n\n==Cast==\n<!-- As shown in the credits, some names differ in dialogue. -->\n\n* [[Cate Blanchett]] as [[Lady Tremaine|Stepmother]], also known as Lady Tremaine\n* [[Lily James]] as [[Cinderella (Disney character)|Cinderella]], also known as Ella\n** Eloise Webb as Ella (10 years old)\n* [[Richard Madden]] as [[Prince Charming (Disney)|Prince]], also known as Kit\n* [[Helena Bonham Carter]] as [[Fairy Godmother (Disney)|Fairy Godmother]]\n* [[Nonso Anozie]] as Captain\n* [[Stellan Skarsg\u00e5rd]] as [[List of Disney's Cinderella characters#Other minor characters|Grand Duke]]\n* [[Sophie McShera]] as [[Drizella Tremaine|Drisella]]\n* [[Holliday Grainger]] as [[Anastasia Tremaine|Anastasia]]\n* [[Derek Jacobi]] as [[List of Disney's Cinderella characters#Other minor characters|King]]\n* [[Ben Chaplin]] as Ella's father\n* [[Hayley Atwell]] as Ella's mother\n* [[Rob Brydon]] as Master Phineus\n* Jana Perez as Princess Chelina of [[Province of Zaragoza|Zaragoza]]\n* [[Alex Macqueen]] as Royal Crier\n*[[Tom Edden]] as Lizard Footman\n\n==Production==\n\n===Development===\nIn May 2010, following the box office success of [[Tim Burton]]'s ''[[Alice in Wonderland (2010 film)|Alice in Wonderland]]'', which was the second-highest-grossing film of 2010 and earned over $1&nbsp;billion at the box office worldwide,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2010&p=.htm |title=2010 Worldwide Grosses |website=[[Box Office Mojo]] |access-date=June 22, 2019}}</ref> [[Walt Disney Pictures]] began developing a new film adaptation of ''Cinderella'', commissioning a [[Disney Live Action Remakes|live-action reimagining]] based on a script by [[Aline Brosh McKenna]] and produced by [[Simon Kinberg]].<ref name=\"deadline092513\">{{cite news|title=Disney Pays Seven-Figures For Aline Brosh McKenna's Live-Action ''Cinderella'' Pitch|url=https://www.deadline.com/2010/05/disney-pays-seven-figures-for-aline-brosh-mckennas-live-action-cinderella-pitch/|accessdate=September 25, 2013|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=May 17, 2010}}</ref> In August 2011, [[Mark Romanek]] was brought on to direct.<ref>{{cite news|title=Disney Courting Mark Romanek To Direct Re-Imagined ''Cinderella''|url=https://www.deadline.com/2011/08/disney-courting-mark-romanek-to-direct-re-imagined-cinderella/|accessdate=September 12, 2013|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=August 12, 2011}}</ref> On February 29, 2012, it was announced that [[Chris Weitz]] would revise McKenna's script.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/a-better-life-chris-weitz-cinderella-295972|title=''A Better Life'' Director Chris Weitz Joins Disney's Live-Action ''Cinderella'' as Writer|author=Kit, Borys|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 29, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/a-better-life-and-twilight-new-moon-direct-chris-weitz-to-rewrite-disneys-cinderella-for-mark-romanek|title=''A Better Life'' And ''Twilight: New Moon'' Director Chris Weitz To Rewrite Disney's ''Cinderella'' For Mark Romanek|author=Lyttelton, Oliver|work=[[Indiewire]]|date=February 29, 2012}}</ref> In January 2013, Romanek left the project due to creative differences, as he was developing a version that was darker than Disney wanted.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/movies/news/a449452/disneys-new-cinderella-loses-director-mark-romanek.html#~oVPvJawX7DMPUv|title=Disney's new ''Cinderella'' loses director Mark Romanek|author=Dibdin, Emma|work=Digital Spy|date=January 8, 2013}}</ref> Later that month, Disney negotiated with [[Kenneth Branagh]] to take over as director.<ref name=\"cbrodesser\">{{cite web |url=https://www.vulture.com/2013/01/disney-negotiating-with-kenneth-branagh-to-replace-romanek-on-cinderella.html |title=Disney Negotiating With Kenneth Branagh to Direct Cinderella |last=Brodesser-Akner |first=Claude |date=January 31, 2013 |website=[[Vulture.com]] |access-date=June 22, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"rjackson\">{{cite web|url=http://gottafilm.com/disneys-cinderella-returning-to-theaters-in-2015/392/|title=Disney's ''Cinderella'' Returning to Theaters in 2015|author=Jackson, Renee|publisher=GottaFilm.com|date=September 16, 2014}}</ref>\n\n[[Cate Blanchett]] was the first actor to sign on, when it was announced in November 2012 that she would be playing Lady Tremaine, Cinderella's evil stepmother.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://deadline.com/2012/11/cate-blanchett-poised-to-join-disneys-new-cinderella-378102/ |title=Cate Blanchett Poised To Join Disney\u2019s New \u2018Cinderella\u2019 |last=Patten |first=Dominic |date=November 27, 2012 |work=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |access-date=June 22, 2019}}</ref> In March 2013, [[Emma Watson]] was in talks to play Cinderella, but a deal could not be worked out.<ref>[http://www.starpulse.com/news/index.php/2013/03/02/emma_watson_in_talks_to_play_cinderell \"Emma Watson In Talks To Play Cinderella In Live-Action Film\"], starpulse.com, March 2, 2013.</ref><ref name=\"mgraser\">Marc Graser, [https://variety.com/2013/film/news/cinderellas-glass-slipper-didnt-fit-emma-watson-1200007282/ \"Cinderella's Glass Slipper Didn't Fit Emma Watson\"], ''Variety'', March 12, 2013.</ref> Watson went on to play [[Belle (Beauty and the Beast)|Belle]] in Disney's 2017 film ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://movieweb.com/beauty-beast-why-emma-watson-chose-instead-cinderella/|title= Why Emma Watson Chose Beauty and the Beast Over Cinderella|last=Scott|first=Ryan|publisher=Movie Web|date=January 17, 2017|access-date=March 26, 2019}}</ref> [[Gabriella Wilde]], [[Saoirse Ronan]], [[Alicia Vikander]], [[Bella Heathcote]] and [[Margot Robbie]] were also considered for the part, but deals could not be worked out due to scheduling and other conflicts.<ref name=\"mgraser\" /><ref>Mike Fleming Jr, [https://deadline.com/2013/04/three-actresses-testing-to-see-if-glass-slipper-fits-for-cinderella-lead-466920/ \"Three Actresses Testing To See If Glass Slipper Fits For ''Cinderella''\"], Deadline.com, April 3, 2013.</ref>\n\nOn April 30, 2013, [[Lily James]] was cast as the titular character.<ref name=\"comingsoon043013\">[https://www.comingsoon.net/news/movienews.php?id=103631 \"Lily James is Disney's Cinderella\"], comingsoon.net, April 30, 2013.</ref><ref name=\"acheney\">Alexandra Cheney, [https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2013/04/30/downton-abbey-star-is-new-cinderella/?KEYWORDS=cinderella+branagh \"''Downton Abbey'' Star is New Cinderella\"], ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'', April 30, 2013.</ref> A week later, [[Richard Madden]] was cast as Prince Charming, who was named Kit in the film.<ref>Sophie Schillaci, [https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cinderella-game-thrones-richard-madden-519557 \"Disney Casts ''Game of Thrones'' Actor as ''Cinderella''{{'}}s Prince\"], ''The Hollywood Reporter'', May 8, 2013.</ref> In June 2013, it was reported that [[Holliday Grainger]] and [[Sophie McShera]] joined the film as Cinderella's two evil stepsisters, Anastasia and Drisella.<ref>Jeff Sneider, [https://www.thewrap.com/movies/column-post/borgias-star-holliday-grainger-talks-join-disneys-cinderella-exclusive-96416/ \"''The Borgias'' Star Holliday Grainger Joins Disney's ''Cinderella''\"], [[TheWrap]], June 10, 2013.</ref><ref>Borys Kit, [https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/downton-abbey-star-talks-join-566353 &#039;Downton Abbey&#039; Star in Talks to Join Disney&#039;s &#039;Cinderella&#039; (Exclusive)], ''The Hollywood Reporter'', June 11, 2013.</ref> Later that month, [[Helena Bonham Carter]] was cast as the Fairy Godmother.<ref name=\"bkit062013\">Borys Kit, [https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/helena-bonham-carter-boards-cinderella-572595 \"Helena Bonham Carter to Play Fairy Godmother in Disney's ''Cinderella''\"], ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', June 20, 2013.</ref> In August 2013, [[Hayley Atwell]] and [[Ben Chaplin]] joined the cast to play Cinderella's mother and Cinderella's father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/movies/news/a508938/hayley-atwell-joins-kenneth-branaghs-cinderella.html?rss|title=Hayley Atwell joins Kenneth Branagh's 'Cinderella'|work=Digital Spy|date=August 22, 2013|accessdate=August 27, 2013}}</ref> In September 2013, [[Stellan Skarsg\u00e5rd]]'s role as the Grand Duke was confirmed.<ref name=\"Disney's Live\">{{cite web|title=DISNEY'S LIVE-ACTION \"CINDERELLA\" BEGINS PRINCIPAL PHOTOGRAPHY IN LONDON|url=http://www.waltdisneystudios.com/corp/news/1399|publisher=The Walt Disney Company|accessdate=September 23, 2013|date=September 23, 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130926211126/http://www.waltdisneystudios.com/corp/news/1399|archivedate=September 26, 2013}}</ref> On September 23, 2013, it was announced that [[Derek Jacobi]] was cast as the King, Prince Kit's father, and [[Nonso Anozie]] as the Captain, a loyal friend to the Prince.<ref name=\"Disney's Live\" />\n\nAccording to Walt Disney Pictures president of production [[Sean Bailey]], studio chairman [[Alan F. Horn]] wished to make the film the \"definitive ''Cinderella'' for generations to come,\" and told him that \"if you need to spend a little more, spend it, to make sure it's one for the time capsule.\"<ref name=\"Rainey\">{{cite news|last1=Rainey|first1=James|title=Disney's Alan Horn Uses Low-Key Approach, Keen Creative Vision to Find Hits of the Future|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/alan-horn-disney-chairman-1201749971/|accessdate=December 14, 2016|work=Variety|publisher=Variety Media|date=April 11, 2016|location=Los Angeles}}</ref>\n\n===Costumes===\nThree-time Oscar-winning costume designer [[Sandy Powell (costume designer)|Sandy Powell]] was in charge of the costumes for the film. Powell began working on concepts for the characters' looks almost two years before principal photography began in the summer of 2013. Powell said she was aiming for the look of \"a nineteenth-century period film made in the 1940s or 1950s.\"<ref name=\"vanityfair.com\">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/hollywood/2015/02/cinderella-wedding-gown-first-look|title=First Look: The Making of Cinderella's Wedding Gown|last=Chi|first=Paul|website=Vanity Fair|date=February 11, 2015|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Vogue\" />\n\nFor the Fairy Godmother, Powell took a major departure from the animated film of the 1950s, instead giving actress [[Helena Bonham Carter]] an opulent white ballgown, featuring fairy wings, puff sleeves and a very full skirt. The skirt also had battery lights underneath it, which Helena said caused issues when filming scenes as the batteries would run low quite quickly.\nFor the stepmother and stepsisters, Powell had a very clear idea about the look; \"They are meant to be totally ridiculous on the outside\u2014a bit too much and overdone\u2014and ugly on the inside.\"<ref name=\"Vogue\">{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com/4463911/cinderella-movie-2015-sandy-powell-costume-designer/|title=What Would Cinderella Wear? Costuming Lily James and Cate Blanchett in Kenneth Branagh's Forthcoming Film|date=November 19, 2014|first=Leslie|last=Camhi|website=Vogue|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref> The silhouette of the prince came from the original animation, however she created a more fitted look and less masculine colors. Some of the prince costumes were dyed to accentuate Madden's eyes.<ref name=\"vanityfair.com\" />\n\nThe ball gown was inspired by the Disney animated film in its color and shape; \"The gown had to look lovely when she dances and runs away from the ball. I wanted her to look like she was floating, like a watercolor painting.\"<ref name=\"vanityfair.com\" /> The dress was made with more than a dozen fine layers of fabric, a corset and a petticoat. Nine versions of the Cinderella gown were designed, each with more than 270 yards of fabric and 10,000 crystals. It took 18 tailors and 500 hours to make each dress.<ref name=\"vanityfair.com\" />\n\nThe wedding dress was another difficult project. \"Creating the wedding dress was a challenge. Rather than try to make something even better than the ball gown, I had to do something completely different and simple... I wanted the whole effect to be ephemeral and fine, so we went with an extreme-lined shaped bodice with a long train\", said Powell. It took 16 people and 550 hours to complete the silk-organza, hand painted dress. While the crew photographed James in the gown, the actress stood too close to an electric heater and the dress caught on fire; the top layer of the dress had to be redone because only one wedding dress was created due to time and budget constraints.<ref name=\"vanityfair.com\" />\n\nFor the glass slipper, Powell took inspiration from a 1950s shoe she saw in a museum. Since glass does not sparkle, they decided to use crystal instead. [[Swarovski]] partnered with Disney to make the famous shoe. Powell went directly to Swarovski headquarters in [[Austria]] to meet the product developers. It took 6 digital renderings of the shoes until they found the right one for the film. Swarovski made eight pairs of crystal shoes for the film, though none were actually wearable. Consequently, the leather shoes James wore on set had to be digitally altered into crystal. Alongside the slipper, Swarovski provided more than 7&nbsp;million crystals that were used in costumes and 100 tiaras for the ball scene.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LGe-3y5EkoU|title=Magic in the Making|publisher=YouTube|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\n[[Principal photography]] on ''Cinderella'' began on September 23, 2013.<ref name=\"Disney's Live\" /> The film was shot at [[Pinewood Studios]] in [[Buckinghamshire, England]], and at various other locations including [[Hampton Court Palace]], [[Blenheim Palace]], [[Windsor Castle]], [[Cliveden]], [[Old Royal Naval College]], and [[Black Park]].<ref name=\"rjackson\" /> Although the royal palace is mainly computer-generated, it has been modeled after the [[Zwinger (Dresden)|Zwinger]] in [[Dresden]], Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnn-online.de/dresden/web/regional/kultur/detail/-/specific/Cinderella-kommt-neu-ins-Kino-der-Dresdner-Zwinger-ist-im-Bild-2664373076|title=Cinderella kommt neu ins Kino \u2013 der Dresdner Zwinger ist im Bild|work=DNN-Online|date=February 25, 2015|access-date=June 24, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150625195028/http://www.dnn-online.de/dresden/web/regional/kultur/detail/-/specific/Cinderella-kommt-neu-ins-Kino-der-Dresdner-Zwinger-ist-im-Bild-2664373076|archive-date=June 25, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Post-production===\nPost-production began in December 2013, and was completed in August 2014.<ref name=\"rjackson\" /> The finished film was rated PG for \"mild thematic elements\" by the [[Motion Picture Association of America]].<ref>{{cite news|title='Cinderella', 'Camp X-Ray', 'November Man' & 'Red Army' in Today's MPAA ratings|url=http://www.ropeofsilicon.com/cinderella-camp-x-ray-november-man-red-army-todays-mpaa-ratings/|accessdate=August 5, 2014|date= August 5, 2014}}</ref> In the United Kingdom, the film received a [[British Board of Film Classification#Current certificates|U classification]] for 'very mild scenes of emotional upset' by the [[British Board of Film Classification]].<ref name=\"BBFC\"/>\n\n==Music==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Cinderella (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack)\n| type       = [[Film score]]\n| artist     = [[Patrick Doyle]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = March 10, 2015\n| recorded   = [[Associated Independent Recording|Air Lyndhurst Studios]] (London)\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Orchestral\n| length     = 84:57\n| label      = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| producer   = [[Kenneth Branagh]]\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n| misc       = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Patrick Doyle]]\n | type       = Soundtrack\n | prev_title = [[Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit#Music|Jack Ryan: Shadow Recruit]]\n | prev_year  = 2014\n | title      = Cinderella\n | year       = 2015\n | next_title =\n | next_year  =\n}}\n}}\n<!-- {{Album ratings\n}} --><!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->\n\nOn June 7, 2013, news confirmed that composer [[Patrick Doyle]] would score the film, with the music having an emphasis on romance.<ref>{{cite news|title=Patrick Doyle to Reunite with Kenneth Branagh on Disney's ''Cinderella''|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2013/06/07/patrick-doyle-to-reunite-with-kenneth-branagh-on-disneys-cinderella/|accessdate=May 16, 2014|publisher=filmmusicreporter.com|date=June 7, 2013}}</ref> Doyle has previously scored several Branagh films, including ''[[Hamlet (1996 film)|Hamlet]]'' and ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/kenneth-branagh-cinderella-shakespeare-jack-ryan/|title=Kenneth Branagh Talks Jack Ryan, Changes Due to Budgetary Reasons, Whether He Will Make Another Shakespeare Movie, Cinderella, and More|publisher=Collider.com|author=Weintraub, Steve|date=January 17, 2014}}</ref> He has also scored the Disney\u00b7[[Pixar]] [[computer animation|computer-animated]] fantasy-comedy film ''[[Brave (2012 film)|Brave]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Walt Disney Records to Release Patrick Doyle's 'Brave' Soundtrack|url=http://filmmusicreporter.com/2012/05/01/walt-disney-records-to-release-patrick-doyles-brave-soundtrack/|website=Film Music Reporter|publisher=Film Music Reporter|accessdate=November 30, 2014}}</ref> Doyle recorded the film's score with the [[London Symphony Orchestra]] conducted by [[James Shearman]] <ref name=\"prnewswire.com\">{{cite news|title=Walt Disney Records Presents The Cinderella Original Motion Picture Soundtrack Available March 10|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/walt-disney-records-presents-the-cinderella-original-motion-picture-soundtrack-available-march-10-300041449.html|accessdate=March 22, 2015|agency=PR Newswire|date=February 22, 2015}}</ref>\nat the [[Associated Independent Recording|Air Lyndhurst Studios]] in London.<ref name=\"prnewswire.com\"/>\n\nThe soundtrack debuted at No. 60 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], selling 8,000 copies in its first week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/entry/view/id/118962|title=Billboard 200 Chart Moves: Marvin Gaye Sales Up 246% After 'Blurred Lines' Trial|author=Keith Caulfield|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=March 21, 2015|accessdate=March 22, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n|collapsed = no\n|total_length = 84:57\n|all_music = \n|headline = \n|extra_column = Performer(s)\n|title1   = A Golden Childhood\n|length1  = 3:56\n|title2   = The Great Secret\n|length2  = 3:01\n|title3   = A New Family\n|length3  = 2:15\n|title4   = Life and Laughter\n|length4  = 1:34\n|title5   = The First Branch\n|length5  = 2:11\n|title6   = Nice and Airy\n|length6  = 1:53\n|title7   = Orphaned\n|length7  = 3:46\n|title8   = The Stag\n|length8  = 4:56\n|title9   = Rich Beyond Reason\n|length9  = 1:43\n|title10  = Fairy Godmother\n|length10 = 2:47\n|title11  = Pumpkins and Mice\n|length11 = 4:32\n|title12  = You Shall Go\n|length12 = 3:02\n|title13  = Valse Royale\n|length13 = 2:06\n|title14  = Who Is She?\n|length14 = 3:20\n|title15  = La Valse De L'amour\n|length15 = 2:34\n|title16  = La Valse Champagne\n|length16 = 1:35\n|title17  = La Polka Militaire\n|length17 = 1:47\n|title18  = La Polka De Paris\n|length18 = 1:22\n|title19  = A Secret Garden\n|length19 = 2:48\n|title20  = La Polka De Minuit\n|length20 = 2:02\n|title21  = Choose That One\n|length21 = 1:16\n|title22  = Pumpkin Pursuit\n|length22 = 2:28\n|title23  = The Slipper\n|length23 = 1:00\n|title24  = Shattered Dreams\n|length24 = 4:10\n|title25  = Searching the Kingdom\n|length25 = 2:51\n|title26  = Ella and Kit\n|length26 = 2:11\n|title27  = Courage and Kindness\n|length27 = 4:38\n|title28  = Strong\n|extra28  = [[Sonna Rele]]\n|writer28 = Patrick Doyle, Kenneth Branagh and [[TommyD|Tommy Danvers]]\n|length28 = 3:14\n|title29  = [[A Dream Is a Wish Your Heart Makes]]\n|extra29  = [[Lily James]]\n|writer29 = [[Al Hoffman]], [[Mack David]], and [[Jerry Livingston]]\n|length29 = 2:00\n|title30  = [[Bibbidi-Bobbidi-Boo|Bibbidi-Bobbidi-Boo (The Magic Song)]]\n|extra30  = [[Helena Bonham Carter]]\n|writer30 = Al Hoffman, Mack David, and Jerry Livingston\n|length30 = 2:28\n|title31  = Strong (Instrumental Version)\n|length31 = 3:14\n|title32  = A Dream Is a Wish Your Heart Makes (Instrumental Version)\n|length32 = 2:01\n|title33  = Bibbidi-Bobbidi-Boo (The Magic Song) (Instrumental Version)\n|length33 = 1:21\n}}\n\n==Release==\nThe film had its world premiere on February 13, 2015, at the [[65th Berlin International Film Festival]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/feb/14/kenneth-branagh-debuts-updated-non-sexist-cinderella-in-berlin-film-festival|title=Kenneth Branagh debuts updated, non-sexist Cinderella in Berlin film festival|work=[[The Guardian]]|author=Connolly, Kate|date=February 14, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"Berlin\">{{cite web|url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/programm/berlinale_programm/datenblatt.php?film_id=201508077|title=Programme \u2013 ''Cinderella''|accessdate=February 12, 2015|publisher=berlinale.de}}</ref> and was released on March 13, 2015.<ref name=\"release\">{{cite news|title=Disney Dates ''Cinderella'' For March 2015|url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/06/cinderella-movie-release-date-march-13-2015-disney/|accessdate=June 25, 2013|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 24, 2013}}</ref> Theatrically, it was accompanied by [[Walt Disney Animation Studios]]' short film ''[[Frozen Fever]]'', featuring the characters from ''[[Frozen (2013 film)|Frozen]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Graser|first=Marc|title=''Frozen Fever'' Short to Debut in Front of Disney's ''Cinderella''|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/frozen-fever-short-to-debut-in-front-of-disney-cinderella-1201369889/|work=Variety|accessdate=December 3, 2014|date=December 3, 2014}}</ref> On February 10, 2015, [[IMAX Corporation]] and Disney announced plans to digitally re-master the film into the [[IMAX]] format and release it in IMAX theaters globally on the scheduled release date.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Evry|first1=Max|title=Disney's ''Cinderella'' to Get an IMAX Release|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/408397-disneys-cinderella-to-get-an-imax-release|accessdate=February 11, 2015|publisher=comingsoon.net|date=February 10, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe first official presentation of the film occurred at Disney's three-day [[D23 (Disney)|D23 Expo]] in August 2013.<ref>Brooks Barnes, [https://www.nytimes.com/2013/08/12/business/media/disney-fans-get-a-sneak-peek-at-coming-films.html?pagewanted=all \"Disney Fans Get a Sneak Peek at Coming Films\"], ''[[The New York Times]]'', August 11, 2013.</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.insidethemagic.net/2013/08/walt-disney-studios-reveal-live-action-films-at-2013-d23-expo-marvel-maleficent-tomorrowland-muppets-saving-mr-banks/|title=Walt Disney Studios reveal live-action films at 2013 D23 Expo: Marvel, Maleficent, Tomorrowland, Muppets, Saving Mr Banks|work=Inside the Magic|date=August 10, 2013|accessdate=September 17, 2014|last=Brigante|first=Ricky}}</ref> The film was previewed at [[CinemaCon]] in [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], in March 2014, with a teaser showing Cinderella hearing about her father's death, meeting the prince while riding through the forest, her mother's ball gown being torn apart by her step-family, and a comedic bit where the Fairy Godmother transforms a pumpkin into a carriage.<ref>Rebecca Ford, [https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cinemacon-disney-debuts-new-trailer-691294 \"CinemaCon: Disney Debuts New Trailer for ''Cinderella''\"], ''The Hollywood Reporter'', March 26, 2014.</ref><ref>Brent Lang, [https://www.thewrap.com/cinderella-offers-cate-blanchett-scenery-chewing-step-mother/ \"''Cinderella'' Peek Offers Cate Blanchett as Evil Stepmother\"], TheWrap, March 26, 2014.</ref>\n\nThe first official trailer debuted on May 15, 2014. In the minute-long teaser, which doesn't include any footage from the film, a sparkling glass slipper is slowly revealed over a black background.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cinderella-teaser-trailer-video-704464|title=Disney's 'Cinderella' Gets Teaser Trailer (Video)|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=May 15, 2014|accessdate=September 17, 2014|last=Ng|first=Philiana}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/news/celebrity/2013/09/24/cinderella-kenneth-branagh-lily-james|title=The first trailer for Disney's ''Cinderella'' movie is here|work=[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]|author=Spencer, Hayley|date=May 16, 2014}}</ref> The second official trailer, two-and-a-half minutes long and containing footage from the film, debuted on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' on November 19, 2014, with a 15-second trailer preview released two days prior.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.movieweb.com/cinderella-movie-trailer-preview-disney-live-action|title=''Cinderella'' Trailer Preview Teases Live-Action Disney Fairy Tale|work=[[MovieWeb]]|last=Gallagher|first=Brian|date=November 17, 2014|accessdate=October 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/598785/cinderella-trailer-debuts-director-sir-kenneth-branagh-opens-up-about-the-live-action-disney-movie|title=Cinderella Trailer Debuts! Director Sir Kenneth Branagh Opens Up About the Live-Action Disney Movie!|publisher=[[E!]]|author=Johnson, Zach|date=November 19, 2014}}</ref> In its first 24 hours of release, the trailer was viewed 4.2&nbsp;million times on [[YouTube]] and 33&nbsp;million times on [[Facebook]], the highest views among all Disney films in history, except for [[Marvel Studios]] releases.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/trailer-report-cinderella-shatters-disney-750772|title=Trailer Report: 'Cinderella' Shatters Disney Record|first1=Pamela|last1=McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=November 20, 2014|accessdate=November 22, 2014}}</ref> The movie's official poster was also released on November 19, featuring James as Cinderella and photographed by [[Annie Leibovitz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/trailers/384421-the-new-trailer-poster-and-photos-for-disneys-cinderella#/slide/1|title=The New Trailer, Poster and Photos for Disney's ''Cinderella''!|publisher=ComingSoon.net|date=November 19, 2014}}</ref> Disney released an international trailer on December 16, 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/trailers/392721-the-new-international-trailer-for-disneys-cinderella#/slide/1|title=The New International Trailer for Disney's ''Cinderella''|first1=Max|last1=Evry|publisher=comingsoon.net|date=December 16, 2014|accessdate=January 16, 2015}}</ref> A new trailer was released on January 1, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://insidemovies.ew.com/2015/01/02/cinderella-gets-midnight-themed-trailer-for-new-years/|title='Cinderella' gets midnight-themed trailer for New Year's|first1=Esther|last1=Zuckerman|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=January 2, 2015|accessdate=January 3, 2015}}</ref> On February 11, 2015, Disney released a final trailer for the film.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lesnick|first1=Silas|title=The New Cinderella Trailer is Here!|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/trailers/408701-the-new-cinderella-trailer-is-here#/slide/1|accessdate=February 11, 2015|publisher=comingsoon.net|date=February 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2014, a licensing agreement between Disney and [[Turner Broadcasting]] was announced, in which ''Cinderella'' would premiere across Turner's cable network portfolio (including [[TBS (U.S. TV channel)|TBS]] and [[TNT (U.S. TV network)|TNT]]) in the Spring of 2017.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ng|first1=Philiana|title=Disney's Live-Action 'Cinderella,' 'Jungle Book' Films Land at Turner Broadcasting|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disneys-cinderella-jungle-book-films-742080|accessdate=October 22, 2014|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=October 20, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\n[[Walt Disney Studios Home Entertainment]] released ''Cinderella'' on Blu-ray combo pack, Digital HD, DVD, and \"Disney Movies Anywhere\" on September 15, 2015.<ref>[http://www.dvdsreleasedates.com/movies/6108/Cinderella-2015.html Cinderella (2015) Blu-ray / DVD release date September 15, 2015] DVDs Release Date, Retrieved September 15, 2015</ref> Blu-ray bonus features include an alternate opening, the ''[[Frozen Fever]]'' short, and the featurettes: \"Staging The Ball\", \"Ella's Furry Friends\", \"A Fairy Tale Comes to Life\", and \"Costume Test Fun\". Five deleted scenes with an introduction by [[Kenneth Branagh]] are included exclusively on \"Disney Movies Anywhere\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Evry|first=Max|title=Cinderella Blu-ray and Digital HD Announced, Watch Alternate Opening|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/dvd/trailers/449773-cinderella-blu-ray-and-digital-hd-announced-watch-alternate-opening#/slide/1|accessdate=June 12, 2015|work=comingsoon.net|date=June 12, 2015}}</ref> The film debuted in second place on the home media sales charts behind ''[[Furious 7]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Arnold|first=Thomas K.|title=''Furious 7'' Speeds to Top of Disc Sales Chart|url=https://variety.com/2015/digital/news/furious-7-speeds-to-top-of-disc-sales-chart-1201601817/|accessdate=September 24, 2015|work=variety.com|date=September 24, 2015}}</ref> Cinderella is scheduled to be released on 4K Blu-Ray on June 25, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ultrahd.highdefdigest.com/73213/cinderella4kultrahdbluray.html|title=Cinderella (2015) - 4K Ultra HD Blu-ray Ultra HD Review {{!}} High Def Digest|website=ultrahd.highdefdigest.com|access-date=May 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n\n===Box office===\n''Cinderella'' grossed $201.2&nbsp;million in the US and Canada, and $341.2&nbsp;million in other countries, for a worldwide total of $542.4&nbsp;million against a budget of $100&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"BOM\" /><ref name=\"filmla\" /> It is the twelfth highest-grossing film of 2015 in any genre.<ref>{{cite web|title=2015 Worldwide Grosses|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?view2=worldwide&yr=2015&p=.htm|website=Box Office Mojo|accessdate=February 7, 2016}}</ref> The film had a worldwide opening of $132.45&nbsp;million,<ref name=\"OP\"/> and an IMAX opening of $9&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"THRR\"/> ''[[Deadline Hollywood]]'' calculated the net profit of the film to be $164.77&nbsp;million, when factoring together all expenses and revenues for the film.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/03/cinderella-movie-profit-2015-box-office-disney-1201724740/|title=No. 8 ''Cinderella'' \u2013 2015 Most Valuable Movie Blockbuster Tournament|author=Mike Fleming Jr|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 23, 2016|accessdate=March 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn the U.S. and Canada, ''Cinderella'' opened on Friday, March 13, 2015, across 3,845 theaters, and earned $23&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"DDD\">{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/03/14/box-office-disneys-cinderella-conjures-23m-friday/|title=Friday Box Office: Disney's 'Cinderella' Conjures $23M For $65M-$75M Weekend|author=Scott Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=March 14, 2015|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> The film's Friday gross included a $2.3&nbsp;million late night run.<ref name=\"DDD\"/> It topped the box office during its opening weekend as projected, earning $67.9&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Subers|first1=Ray|title=Weekend Report: 'Cinderella' Shines, 'Run' Stumbles|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4043&p=.htm|accessdate=March 15, 2015|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|date=March 15, 2015}}</ref> including a record $5&nbsp;million from 358 [[IMAX]] theaters, and became Disney's biggest 2D PG-rated opening of all time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/03/15/box-office-cinderella-goes-bippity-boppity-boom-for-70m-weekend/|title=Box Office: 'Cinderella' Goes Bippity Boppity Boom For $70M Weekend|author=Scott Mendelson|work=[[Forbes]]|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4043&p=.htm|title=Weekend Report: 'Cinderella' Shines, 'Run' Stumbles|author=Ray Subers|website=Box Office Mojo|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref> It is director Kenneth Branagh's biggest opening of his career (breaking 2011's ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'' record), the fourth-highest Disney opening in March,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/03/cinderella-weekend-box-office-liam-neeson-run-all-night-1201392631/|title=''Cinderella''{{'}}s Glamorous Weekend: $70.1M Box Office Opening \u2013 First Sunday Update|author=Nancy Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref> and was the seventh-highest opening in March overall (not counting for inflation).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/month/?mo=03&p=.htm|title=TOP OPENING WEEKENDS BY MONTH - APRIL|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=March 15, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150316054849/http://www.boxofficemojo.com/alltime/weekends/month/?mo=03&p=.htm|archivedate=March 16, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"NAopeningBO\">{{cite news|title=NORTH AMERICA: Weekend Estimates: 'Cinderella' Arrives at the Box Office Ball with a Strong $70.1M; 'Run All Night' a Distant Second with a Modest $11.0M|url=http://pro.boxoffice.com/latest-news/2015-03-13-north-america-thursday-night-report-cinderella-draws-strong-23m-from-early-shows-2|accessdate=March 15, 2015|work=[[Boxoffice (magazine)|Boxoffice.com]]|date=March 14, 2015}}</ref> Audiences during its opening weekend comprised 66% female, 66% families, 26% adults, 8% teenagers, 31% under the age of 12 and 9% 50 years and older.<ref name=\"THRR\"/> ''Cinderella'' finished its first week at the box office with $87.55&nbsp;million, which was very high end of the film's lofty pre-release expectations.<ref>{{cite news|title=NORTH AMERICA: 'Cinderella' Impresses With $87.55M In Its First Week After Ruling Thursday With $4.47M|url=http://pro.boxoffice.com/latest-news/2015-03-20-north-america-cinderella-impresses-with-8755m-in-its-first-week-after-ruling-thursday-with-447m|accessdate=March 29, 2015|work=[[Boxoffice (magazine)|Boxoffice.com]]|date=March 20, 2015}}</ref> In its [[Second weekend in box office performance|second weekend]], the film declined 49% to $35&nbsp;million and was surpassed by ''[[The Divergent Series: Insurgent]]'', dropping to #2.<ref name=\"weekend\">{{cite web|title=Cinderella (2015) - Weekend Box Office Results&nbsp;\u2014 Box Office Mojo|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=weekend&id=cinderella2015.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=March 29, 2015}}</ref> The drop was in between two of Disney's previous live-action fantasy films, ''[[Oz the Great and Powerful]]'' (48%) and ''[[Maleficent (film)|Maleficent]]'' (51%).<ref>{{cite news|last1=Subers|first1=Ray|title=Weekend Report: 'Insurgent' Surges to $52.3 Million, 'Gunman' Bombs|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/news/?id=4047&p=.htm|accessdate=March 22, 2015|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[Internet Movie Database]]|date=March 29, 2015}}</ref> In North America, ''Cinderella'' is the ninth highest-grossing 2015 film.<ref>{{cite web|title=2015 Yearly Box Office Results - 2015 Domestic Grosses|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?yr=2015&p=.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=February 3, 2016}}</ref>\n\nOutside North America, box office analysts predicted as much as $60&nbsp;million opening.<ref name=\"OT\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/03/cinderella-box-office-liam-neeson-run-all-night-1201390746/|title=''Cinderella'' To Cast $100M-$120M Spell In Global Debut&nbsp;\u2013 Box Office Preview|author=Nancy Tartaglione and Anthony D'Alessandro|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 11, 2015|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref> The film made its debut outside of North America on the same weekend as its wide North American release and earned an estimated $62.4&nbsp;million from 31 countries,<ref name=\"OP\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/03/cinderella-international-box-office-china-biggest-march-opening-disney-1201392972/|title=''Cinderella'' Waltzes Onto World Stage With $62.4M Offshore Bow; $132M Global|author=Nancy Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref> including $4&nbsp;million from IMAX theaters.<ref name=\"THRR\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-cinderella-lives-happily-781558|title=Box Office: 'Cinderella' Lives Happily Ever After With $132.5M Global Debut|author=Pamela McClintock|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=March 15, 2015}}</ref> It topped the box office for two non-consecutive weekends.<ref name=\"CINDERELLA\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/03/cinderella-leads-international-weekend-box-office-kingsman-china-home-get-hard-1201400720/|title=''Cinderella'' Returns To Top Of Offshore Box Office; ''Home'' Brings $49M+ To Pass $100M Worldwide \u2013 Update|author=Nancy Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 29, 2015|accessdate=March 30, 2015}}</ref> It opened in China with $25&nbsp;million, the biggest March opening in the country,<ref name=\"OP\"/> and Russia with $7.3&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"OP\"/> The opening in these two countries were considered impressive given that both the countries are famous for their keenness for 3D films rather than 2D.<ref name=\"OP\"/> Other high openings occurred in the UK, Ireland and Malta ($5.6&nbsp;million), Mexico ($5&nbsp;million), Japan ($4.8&nbsp;million), France ($3.3&nbsp;million), and Brazil ($3.7&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"CINDERELLA\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/04/ultron-furious-cinderella-japan-home-china-international-box-office-1201416669/|title=''Ultron'', ''Furious'' Lead As ''Cinderella'' Scores In Japan: International B.O. Update|author=Nancy Tartaglione|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=([[Penske Media Corporation]])|date=April 27, 2015|accessdate=May 3, 2015}}</ref> In Australia, where the release date was coinciding with the [[2015 Cricket World Cup|Cricket World Cup finale]], it managed to open with $3.4&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"CINDERELLA\"/> Italy opened with $4.6&nbsp;million and topped the box office for three consecutive weekends.<ref name=\"OP\"/><ref name=\"CINDERELLA\"/> It also topped the Japanese box office for five consecutive weekends.<ref name=\"JOX\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/japan-box-office-cinderella-top-797840|title=Japan Box Office: 'Cinderella' Spends Fifth Weekend on Top|author=Gavin J. Blair|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=([[Prometheus Global Media]])|date=May 25, 2015|accessdate=May 25, 2015}}</ref> It became the second-highest grossing Disney live-action film in China, behind ''[[Pirates of the Caribbean: On Stranger Tides]]'' and in the Philippines, behind ''[[Maleficent (film)|Maleficent]]''.<ref name=\"DL\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/03/international-box-office-insurgent-home-gunman-cinderella-kingsman-1201396540/|title=''Insurgent'' Tops Overseas Box Office; DWA's ''Home'' Runs Up $19M \u2013 Update|author=Nancy Tartaglione|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=March 22, 2015|accessdate=March 23, 2015}}</ref> In total earnings, its largest markets outside of the US and Canada are China ($71.1&nbsp;million), Japan ($46&nbsp;million) and the UK, Ireland and Malta ($29.2&nbsp;million).<ref name=\"JOX\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/05/cinderella-passes-500-million-worldwide-for-disney-1201421720/|title=''Cinderella'' Crosses $500M Worldwide for Disney|author=Anita Busch|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|publisher=([[Penske Media Corporation]])|date=May 6, 2015|accessdate=May 7, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/japan-box-office-tomorrowland-unseated-802419|title=Japan Box Office: Anime Film Unseats 'Tomorrowland,' 'Cinderella' Passes $45 Million|author=Gavin J. Blair|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|publisher=([[Prometheus Global Media]])|date=June 15, 2015|accessdate=June 15, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Critical response===\n''Cinderella'' received positive<!--NOTE: Do not add \"critically acclaimed\" without a WP:Reliable source supporting it.--> reviews from critics with particular praise going to the cast, notably Blanchett, James, and Bonham Carter, Patrick Doyle's musical score, faithfulness to the original animated film, and Sandy Powell's costume designs.<ref name=\"Barnes\">{{cite web|last=Barnes|first=Brooks|title=Forget the Ball, ''Cinderella'' Is the Belle of the Box Office|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=March 15, 2015|accessdate=December 24, 2015|url=http://artsbeat.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/03/15/forget-the-ball-cinderella-is-the-belle-of-the-box-office/}}</ref> On [[review aggregator]] website [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film holds an 84% approval rating, based on 242 reviews, with a [[rating average]] of 7.16/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"Refreshingly traditional in a revisionist era, Kenneth Branagh's ''Cinderella'' proves Disney hasn't lost any of its old-fashioned magic.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/cinderella_2013/|title=Cinderella|website=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=October 26, 2019}}</ref> [[Metacritic]] assigned the film a weighted average score of 67 out of 100, based on 47 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/cinderella|title=Cinderella Reviews|website=Metacritic|accessdate=December 22, 2015}}</ref> According to [[CinemaScore]], audiences gave the film a grade of \"A\" on an A+ to F scale.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cinemascore.com/|title=CinemaScore|publisher=CinemaScore|accessdate=July 15, 2015}}</ref>\n\nDavid Rooney of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' reviewed the film at the Berlin Film Festival and praised the special effects, the screenplay, and Blanchett's performance and said that \"anyone nostalgic for childhood dreams of transformation will find something to enjoy in an uplifting movie that invests warm sentiment in universal themes of loss and resilience, experience and maturity.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/entry/view/id/914145|title = 'Cinderella': Berlin Review|author =Rooney, David|work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date = February 14, 2015|accessdate = February 14, 2015}}</ref> Peter Debruge of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' said, \"It's all a bit square, big on charm, but lacking the crackle of ''Enchanted'' or ''The Princess Bride''. But though this ''Cinderella'' could never replace Disney's animated classic, it's no ugly stepsister either, but a deserving companion.\"<ref>{{cite web|url = https://variety.com/2015/film/reviews/berlin-film-review-disneys-new-live-action-cinderella-1201433243/|title = Berlin Film Review: 'Cinderella'|author = Debruge, Peter|work =[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date = February 13, 2015|accessdate = February 14, 2015}}</ref> Guy Lodge of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film three stars out of five and said, \"While it might have been nice to see the new-model ''Cinderella'' follow ''Frozen''{{'s}} progressive, quasi-feminist lead, the film's naff, preserved-in-amber romanticism is its very charm.\"<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/feb/13/cinderella-review-kenneth-branaghs-perky-pretty-cupcake-of-a-fairytale|title = Cinderella review \u2013 Kenneth Branagh's perky, pretty cupcake of a fairytale|author =Lodge, Guy|work =[[The Guardian]]|location=London|date = February 13, 2015|accessdate = February 15, 2015}}</ref> Scott Mendelson of ''[[Forbes]]'' admired the film's visual effects, production design, and called the costume design as Oscar-worthy, adding, \"with an emphasis on empathy and empowerment, Walt Disney's ''Cinderella'' is the best film yet in their 'turn our animated classics into live-action blockbuster' subgenre.\"<ref>{{cite web|url =https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2015/02/23/review-disneys-cinderella-is-the-fairest-of-them-all/|title=Review: Disney's 'Cinderella' Is the Fairest of Them All|author=Mendelson, Scott|work=[[Forbes]]|date=February 23, 2015|accessdate=February 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[Richard Corliss]] of ''[[Time (magazine)|Time]]'' magazine said that Branagh's ''Cinderella'' successfully updates and revitalizes Disney's \"ill-conceived\" animated film, and praised the empowered Ella, the visuals, and Blanchett's performance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://time.com/3743894/cinderella-review-disney-live-action/|title=Review: Disney's Live-Action ''Cinderella'' Rekindles Old Studio Magic|author=Corliss, Richard|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=March 13, 2015|accessdate=March 25, 2015}}</ref> Katy Waldman of ''[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]'' similarly deemed the film a commendable and authentic upgrade that does not undermine its heroine while maintaining its classic splendor and charm.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slate.com/articles/arts/movies/2015/03/live_action_2015_cinderella_movie_from_kenneth_branagh_reviewed.html|title=Ashes to Sashes|work=[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]|author=Waldman, Katy|date=March 12, 2015|accessdate=March 25, 2015}}</ref> [[Joe Morgenstern]] of ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' commended James' and Blanchett's performances, the sets, costumes and minimal digital effects, as well as Branagh's direction, stating he \"set a tone of lushly sustainable fantasy that's often affecting, frequently witty, seldom cloying, nearly free of self-comment and entirely free of irony.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/cinderella-review-finds-new-soul-in-old-shoe-1426187867|title=''Cinderella'' Review: Finding New Soul in Old Shoe|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|author=Morgenstern, Joe|date=March 12, 2015|accessdate=March 25, 2015}}</ref> Likewise, Claudia Puig of ''[[USA Today]]'' complimented the performances along with Branagh and screenwriter Chris Weitz for \"ground[ing] this romantic tale with sincerity amid the dazzle.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2015/02/28/cinderella-disney-movie-review/24129149/|title=Review: Remake is true 'Cinderella' story|work=[[USA Today]]|author=Puig, Claudia|date=February 28, 2015|accessdate=March 25, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''{{'}} Betsy Sharkey praised Blanchett's and James' performances and considered the film a \"poetically, if not prophetically, imagined storybook fable\" that succeeds because of its earnestness, humor, its lack of modern-day pretenses, and Branagh's \"singular focus\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-cinderella-20150313-column.html?|title=In 'Cinderella,' no sly asides. Goodness and romance rule|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|author=Sharkey, Betsy|date=March 12, 2015|accessdate=March 25, 2015}}</ref> Lawrence Toppman of ''[[The Charlotte Observer]]'' proclaimed, \"This version has more psychological depth than usual and answers questions we may always have had. Branagh's 'Cinderella' does something extraordinarily rare among fairy-tale adaptations: It leaves out nothing we want and adds nothing we don't.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/entertainment/ent-columns-blogs/lawrence-toppman/article13485305.html|title=Movie review: Sumptuous, subtle ''Cinderella'' satisfies in every way|work=The Charlotte Observer|author=Toppman, Lawrence|date=March 11, 2015|accessdate=March 25, 2015}}</ref> Noting the religious themes and symbols of the film, cultural commentator [[Fr. Robert Barron]] writes that due to Branagh's traditional telling of the story, \"he actually allows the spiritual -- indeed specifically Christian -- character of the tale to emerge.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barron|first1=Robert|title=A Very Christian Cinderella|url=http://www.realclearreligion.org/articles/2015/03/20/a_very_christian_emcinderellaem.html|website=Real Clear Religion|accessdate=March 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe film is #1 on [[TheWrap]]'s list of \"Every Disney Live-Action Remake of an Animated Classic Ranked, Worst to Best\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/disney-live-action-remake-animated-classic-ranked-worst-best-cinderella-aladdin/|title=All 17 Disney Live-Action Remakes of Animated Classics, Ranked from Worst to Best (Photos)|author=William Bibbiani|publisher=[[TheWrap]]|date=November 17, 2019|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref> and is #3 on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] list of \"All 14 Disney Live-Action Remakes Ranked\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/all-disney-live-action-remakes-ranked/|title=All 14 Disney Live-Action Remakes Ranked|author=|publisher=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date=|accessdate=January 8, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Accolades===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width: 100%;\"\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#ccc; text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\"| Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"| Result \n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"| International Online Cinema Halfway Awards\n|rowspan=\"5\"| July 30, 2015\n| Best Supporting Actress\n| [[Cate Blanchett]]\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title='Mad Max: Fury Road' Wins 10 INOCA Halfway Awards, 'Clouds of Sils Maria' \u2013 3 |url=http://awardswatch.com/2015/07/30/mad-max-fury-road-wins-10-inoca-halfway-awards-clouds-of-sils-maria-3/ |website=AwardsWatch |accessdate=June 24, 2018 |date=July 30, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Adapted Screenplay\n| [[Chris Weitz]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Makeup and Hairstyling\n| ''Cinderella''\n| {{nom}}\n|- \n| Best Costume Design\n| [[Sandy Powell (costume designer)|Sandy Powell]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Production Design\n| [[Dante Ferretti]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"| [[2015 Teen Choice Awards|August 16, 2015]]\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| ''Cinderella''\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Staff |first1=Variety |title=Teen Choice Awards 2015 Winners: Full List |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/teen-choice-awards-winners-2015-full-list-1201571268/ |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |accessdate=June 24, 2018 |date=August 17, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Actress \u2013 Sci-Fi/Fantasy|Choice Movie Actress: Sci-Fi/Fantasy]]\n| [[Lily James]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[World Soundtrack Awards]]\n| October 24, 2015\n| [[World Soundtrack Award for Best Original Score of the Year|Best Original Score of the Year]]\n| [[Patrick Doyle]]\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"WSA\">{{cite web |title=Winners of the 15th World Soundtrack Awards |url=https://www.worldsoundtrackawards.com/en/news/winners-of-the-15th-world-soundtrack-awards/24-10-2015/2087 |website=[[World Soundtrack Awards]] |accessdate=June 24, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Hollywood Film Awards]]\n| November 1, 2015\n| Costume Designer of the Year\n| Sandy Powell\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/2015-hollywood-film-awards-winners/|title=2015 Hollywood Film Awards winners|website=[[CBS News]]|date=November 1, 2015|accessdate=December 4, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Hollywood Music in Media Awards]]\n| November 11, 2015\n| Best Original Score - Fantasy Film\n| Patrick Doyle\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6760930/hollywood-music-in-media-awards | title=Hollywood Music in Media Awards: 'Hunting Ground,' 'Furious 7,' '50 Shades of Grey' Claim Top Prizes | work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] | date=November 12, 2015 | accessdate=November 3, 2016 |author=Feinberg, Scott}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards 2015|December 7, 2015]]\n| Best Art Direction\n| {{unbulleted list|Dante Ferretti|Francesca Lo Schiavo}}\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wafca.com/awards/2015.htm |title=2015 WAFCA Award Winners |publisher