gle Book]]'', ''[[Beauty and the Beast (2017 film)|Beauty and the Beast]]'', ''[[Christopher Robin (film)|Christopher Robin]]'', ''[[Dumbo (2019 film)|Dumbo]]'', ''[[Aladdin (2019 film)|Aladdin]]'', ''[[The Lion King (2019 film)|The Lion King]]'', and ''[[Lady and the Tramp (2019 film)|Lady and the Tramp]]'' {{nsmdns}} [[Walt Disney Pictures]] has announced the development of several other live-action remakes from their [[List of Walt Disney Animation Studios films|Animated Classics series]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/04/cinderella-box-office-400-million-worldwide-1201405180/|title=''Cinderella'' Is Having A Ball Worldwide With $400M Box Office|accessdate=April 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2013/07/disney-live-action-jungle-book-reboot-537431/|title=Justin Marks To Adapt Live-Action 'Jungle Book' Reboot At Disney|author=The Deadline Team|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=July 9, 2013|accessdate=September 2, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2014/film/news/bill-condon-beauty-and-the-beast-disney-1201151834/|title=Bill Condon to Direct Live-Action ''Beauty and the Beast'' Film for Disney (EXCLUSIVE)|author=Justin Kroll|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=June 4, 2014|accessdate=April 9, 2015|quote=With the recent release of ''Maleficent'', which grossed more than $170 million worldwide in its opening weekend, Disney is working fast on its next live-action fairy-tale adaptation.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/04/02/disney-develop-live-action-adaptation-winnie-pooh|title=Disney developing live-action adaptation of Winnie the Pooh|accessdate=April 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/tim-burton-to-direct-live-action-dumbo-for-disney-1201449920/|title=Tim Burton to Direct Live-Action ''Dumbo'' for Disney|accessdate=April 10, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disneys-live-action-aladdin-enlists-936881|title=Disney's Live-Action 'Aladdin' Enlists Guy Ritchie to Direct|work=The Hollywood Reporter|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=October 10, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/770967-jon-favreau-to-direct-live-action-lion-king-movie|title=Jon Favreau to Direct Live-Action Lion King Movie!|publisher=Comingsoon.net|last=Evry|first=Max|date=September 28, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/lady-tramp-remake-be-directed-by-charlie-bean-1094301|title='Lego Ninjago Movie' Director Tackling Live-Action 'Lady and the Tramp' (Exclusive)|magazine=Hollywood Reporter|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=March 19, 2018}}</ref> Since the releases of these nine films, Disney has announced the development of live-action adaptations of ''[[Mulan (2020 film)|Mulan]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/mulan-disney-live-action-movie-remake/|title=''Mulan'' Live-Action Movie Being Developed by Disney|accessdate=April 10, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Pinocchio (1940 film)|Pinocchio]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2015/04/pinocchio-inspired-live-action-film-being-developed-at-disney-1201406564/|title=''Pinocchio''-Inspired Live-Action Film Being Developed At Disney|accessdate=April 10, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Fantasia (1940 film)|Fantasia]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/disney-developing-fantasia-sequence-into-live-action-movie-1201511401/|title=Disney Developing ''Fantasia'' Sequence Into Live-Action Movie|accessdate=June 3, 2015}}</ref> ''[[The Sword in the Stone (1963 film)|The Sword in the Stone]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/463581-disney-developing-live-action-the-sword-in-the-stone-remake-from-game-of-thrones-writer|title=Disney Developing Live-Action The Sword in the Stone Remake|accessdate=July 20, 2015}}</ref> ''[[The Black Cauldron (film)|The Black Cauldron]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/film/news/chronicles-of-prydain-movie-disney-1201733058/|title=''Chronicles of Prydain'' Movie in the Works at Disney (EXCLUSIVE)|accessdate=March 31, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Peter Pan (1953 film)|Peter Pan]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/676201-disney-preparing-live-action-peter-pan-with-petes-dragon-director#/slide/1|title=Disney Preparing Live-Action Peter Pan with Pete's Dragon Director|author=Max Evry|accessdate=April 13, 2016}}</ref> ''[[The Little Mermaid (1989 film)|The Little Mermaid]]'',<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/16/little-mermaid-lin-manuel-miranda-alan-menken|title=Lin-Manuel Miranda, Alan Menken team up for live-action Little Mermaid|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|last=Snetiker|first=Marc|date=August 16, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937 film)|Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs]],''<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/10/31/disney-live-action-snow-white-movie|title=Disney planning a live-action Snow White movie|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|last=Coggan|first=Devan|date=October 31, 2016}}</ref> ''[[Lilo & Stitch]]'',<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/lilo-stitch-live-action-disney-remake-works-1148811|title='Lilo & Stitch' Live-Action Remake in the Works at Disney (Exclusive)|magazine=Hollywood Reporter|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=October 3, 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Hunchback of Notre Dame (1996 film)|The Hunchback of Notre Dame]]'',<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/01/16/disney-hunchback-live-action-musical/|title=Disney working on live-action remake of Hunchback of Notre Dame|magazine=Entertainment Weekly|last=Romano|first=Nick|date=January 16, 2019}}</ref> ''[[Bambi]]''<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/bambi-remake-works-1272457|title='Bambi' Remake in the Works With 'Captain Marvel', 'Chaos Walking' Writers (Exclusive)|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|last1=Kit|first1=Borys|last2=Galuppo|first2=Mia|date=January 24, 2020}}</ref> and ''[[Robin Hood (1973 film)|Robin Hood]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/robin-hood-remake-works-at-disney-blindspotting-director-1289702|title='Robin Hood' Remake in the Works at Disney+ With 'Blindspotting' Director (Exclusive)|magazine=The Hollywood Reporter|last=Kit|first=Borys|date=April 10, 2020}}</ref> The company also has plans for live-action spin-offs of ''[[Peter Pan (1953 film)|Peter Pan]]'', ''[[Cruella (film)|One Hundred and One Dalmatians]]'' and ''[[Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1937 film)#Live-action adaptations|Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs]]'' along with live-action prequels to ''[[Aladdin (1992 Disney film)|Aladdin]]'' and the original ''[[Cinderella (1950 film)|Cinderella]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/21/reese-witherspoon-tinker-bell-disney-developing-peter-pan-spinoff-tink|title=Reese Witherspoon as Tinker Bell: Disney developing 'Peter Pan' spinoff 'Tink'|accessdate=May 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/cruella-fifty-shades-writer-kelly-830467|title='Fifty Shades' Writer Kelly Marcel Tackling Disney's Live-Action 'Cruella' (Exclusive)|accessdate=October 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/disney-plans-live-action-film-879528|title=Disney Plans Live-Action Film About Snow White's Sister (Exclusive)|accessdate=March 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.comingsoon.net/movies/news/462369-aladdin-prequel-genie-in-development-at-disney|title=Aladdin Prequel, Genies, in Development at Disney|accessdate=July 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thedisinsider.com/2019/09/22/exclusive-new-details-for-godmothered-film-coming-to-disney/|title=EXCLUSIVE: New Details for \u2018Godmothered\u2019 Film Coming to Disney+|accessdate=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote}}\n{{Portal|Film|United States|Disney}}\n*{{Official website|http://movies.disney.com/cinderella}}\n*{{IMDb title|1661199|Cinderella}}\n*{{mojo title|cinderella2015|Cinderella}}\n*{{rotten-tomatoes|cinderella_2013|Cinderella}}\n*{{metacritic film|cinderella|Cinderella}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=''Cinderella''|state=collapsed\n|list1=\n{{Cinderella (Fairy tale)}}\n{{Disney's Cinderella}}\n{{Disney Princess}}\n{{Disney's live-action adaptations of animated franchises}}\n{{Kenneth Branagh}}\n{{Chris Weitz}}\n{{Allison Shearmur}}\n{{Saturn Award for Best Fantasy Film}}\n}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cinderella 2015}}\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2010s historical romance films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy drama films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American historical fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American historical romance films]]\n[[Category:American romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:American romantic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:British fantasy drama films]]\n[[Category:British films]]\n[[Category:British historical fantasy films]]\n[[Category:British historical romance films]]\n[[Category:British romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:British romantic fantasy films]]\n[[Category:Cinderella (franchise)]]\n[[Category:Disney film remakes]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about fairies and sprites]]\n[[Category:Films about royalty]]\n[[Category:Films about weddings]]\n[[Category:Films about wish fulfillment]]\n[[Category:Films based on adaptations]]\n[[Category:Films based on Charles Perrault's Cinderella]]\n[[Category:Films based on multiple works]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Kenneth Branagh]]\n[[Category:Films produced by David Barron]]\n[[Category:Films produced by Simon Kinberg]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Patrick Doyle]]\n[[Category:Films set in the 19th century]]\n[[Category:Films set in France]]\n[[Category:Films shot at Pinewood Studios]]\n[[Category:Films shot in London]]\n[[Ca